title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix well together the first 6 ingredients.
Bake as you would any corn bread in a skillet or baking pan.
Cool, so you can crumble or break into small pieces.

title: broiled chicken wings
directions: Cut off wing tips.
Cut each wing in half at the joint.
In bowl, mix soy sauce, sherry, oil, paprika, pepper sauce and garlic.
Stir to mix.
Cover loosely and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Broil 4-inches from heat for 14 minutes or until tender.
Brush with marinade.
Serve hot or cold (will keep 3 days).

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together	butter and flour.
Beat eggs and add to the mixture.
Add
sugar, small amount at a time.
Flavor with nutmeg, almond,
lemon
and vanilla extract.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Mix together Bisquick, cheese spread, onions, egg and Italian seasoning until moist.
Stir in 2/3 cup chopped pepperoni.
Spread in pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Good with soup.

title: onion supper bread
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Prepare mix according to package directions.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cooked onion.
Mix sour cream and cheese; spoon over the top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done. Let stand a few minutes; cut in 9 squares.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: chinese food
directions: Put oil in pan or wok.
Add onions, pepper, cauliflower, broccoli, water chestnuts, mushrooms, tomatoes and snow peas. Cook about 8 minutes.
Stir.
Add chicken bouillon, soy sauce, water and cornstarch mixture and meat.
Cook about 10 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: noodle egg drop soup
directions: Bring chicken broth and water to boil; gradually add noodles, stirring occasionally.
Cook 8 minutes.
Reduce heat to low; stir 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; stir in parsley and butter.

title: my favorite sweet dough for poppy seed or nut rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Melt butter with milk and water.
Add sugar, eggs, salt and the dissolved yeast (all at room temperature).
Add flour 1 cup at a time until dough no longer sticks to hands.
Cover dough with a towel and let rise in warm area until dough doubles in size.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: carrot pie
directions: Blend together carrots and eggs.
Combine brown sugar, salt and spices.
Stir into carrot mixture.
Blend in milk.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake about 30 minutes or until sharp knife, inserted near center of custard comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: miniature peanut butter treats(tarts)
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs, peanut butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill.
When cold enough to handle, roll in small (walnut-size) balls.
Place each ball in a greased miniature muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Remove from oven and gently press 1 peanut butter cup into each cookie.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Yields about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: famous hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; it should be a little thinner than cookie dough. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into 325° to 350° oil. Cook for 5 minutes.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: In a large skillet, crumble together the beef and sausage. Cook over medium heat, stirring until meat is browned.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is limp.
Drain off fat.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in clam juice from canned clams and bottle. Cook only until tender (not mushy).
While potatoes are cooking, saute onion in butter until golden.
Add to potatoes with clams, half and half, salt, pepper, cream and dill.
Simmer until hot. Do not overcook.
Substitute haddock or cusk to make fish chowder.

title: banana spice bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Beat together the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in bananas, milk and eggs.
Gradually add combined dry ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake for 70 to 75 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Serve with cinnamon butter or other flavored butters or fruit preserves.
Makes one loaf (18 slices).

title: purple cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and onions.
Mix together salt, celery seed, sugar, oil and vinegar and bring to a boil.
Cook about 5 minutes. Let cool.
Pour over cabbage and onions.
Mix thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
This will keep about 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: This casserole is done in layers, one on top of the other. Boil the chicken breasts covered in water on the stove with a slice of onion, salt and pepper until it falls off the bone.
Pull chicken off the bone and cut into chunks.
Remember to save your cooking water from the chicken and use as broth for the casserole. Dice up the onion and the green pepper and mix together.
Mix the two soups together.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together. Mix well.
Heat oven to 350 degrees and cook until brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix and press into loaf dish.
Refrigerate.

title: orange pecan cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in next eight ingredients.
Blend in flour. Chill and roll in balls.
Then dip in egg whites and roll in coconut.
Press cherry on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage and gravy
directions: In a large skillet, crumble 1/2 pound sausage and cook until browned.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons flour over the browned sausage, stirring constantly.
When the mixture is smooth, slowly add 2 cups milk and continue to cook, stirring constantly, for about 3 minutes until the gravy is creamy and bubbly.
Serve over cut open biscuits or mashed potato.

title: meatball and lima bean bake
directions: Place lima beans in a colander and run hot water over them. Drain and pour into 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine beef with next 6 ingredients.
Shape into 2-inch balls and brown lightly in skillet in oil.
Place in casserole over beans.
Brown the onions in the skillet, place in casserole.
Heat tomato sauce and water, pour over contents.
Top with pepper rings and Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: Crush vanilla wafers to a powder.
Grease pan slightly and spread wafers for pastry.
Mix milk, egg yolks, grated lemon rind and the juice of lemon.
Place on the pastry sheet.
Beat egg white until stiff; place on pie and brown.
Pie is completely prepared before baking the whites of eggs.

title: apple cake
directions: Into a mixing bowl, sift flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and sugar.
Mix well and add cooking oil and eggs.
Beat well. Add vanilla.
Last, add chopped apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 9-inch tube pan or 3 small loaf pans.
If loaf pans are used, cook 45 minutes.

title: fiesta corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, syrup and water.
Bring to a boil; cook until thick and clear.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Cool. Pour over strawberries in baked pie shell.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Soak overnight in cold water.
Heat oil, saute onion and garlic in soup kettle.
Add beans and soaking water, bay leaf and salt.
I add chicken base and 2 strips of lean bacon. Simmer until beans are tender.
Remove 2 cups of beans without liquid to blender.
Drain tomato liquid into blender and puree with beans until smooth.
Chop tomatoes.
Return pureed beans, tomatoes and parsley to soup.
Season to taste with more salt and pepper.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Put lemon or pineapple juice or Fruit-Fresh to keep fruit from turning brown.

title: aztec sauce
directions: Comb all ingredients in blender. Let stand several hr. to allow flavors to mingle.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve with Mexican food.
Especially good as appetizer with cocktail size frozen beef tacos.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine ingredients one at a time in order listed.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze at least 6 hours or overnight. Serve slightly thawed.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until crumbly; stir in milk.
Pat out on floured surface.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake 12 minutes in 450° oven on greased cookie sheet until golden brown.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Add flour and milk, then cheese, mixed vegetables and mushrooms.
Place in casserole dish and put crushed soda crackers on top.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pear pecan salad
directions: Drain pears, reserving 1 cup of juice.
Bring juice to a boil and remove; add Jell-O and chill until partially set.
Blend pears and cheese in blender until creamy .
Stir in Jell-O and pecans. Whip the cream and fold in with other ingredients.
Pour into a large mold or 16 individual molds.
Serves 16.

title: low-fat cranberry and apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine apples, cranberries and granulated sugar.
Spread in a shallow 2-quart casserole or a 10-inch square pan.
In a medium sized bowl, blend brown sugar, oatmeal, flour and spices.
Pour melted margarine over oatmeal mixture; blend well.
Spread topping over fruit. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 servings; each serving contains 6 grams of fat.

title: puffy egg bake
directions: Layer bread, then sausage and cheese and again and again in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix 4 eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt.
Pour over layers and top with cheese.
Let set overnight in refrigerator. Mix 1 can cream of mushroom soup with 1 can water; pour over entire pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Makes a lot.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream margarine, vegetable shortening and add sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add alternately with flour.
Beat well.
Add coconut, nuts and Watkins extracts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans, using 2 cups batter for each pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together one at a time.
Store in refrigerator in tight container.
Serve with raw pepper, cucumbers, celery, cauliflower and carrots.

title: chewy oatmeal raisin bars
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg, flour, vanilla, baking soda and salt.
Stir in oats, walnuts and raisins.
Turn into greased 9-inch square pan. Spread evenly.
Bake in preheated oven at 400°, uncovered, for 12 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Boil cabbage 5 minutes and drain.
Melt 2 teaspoons margarine and add flour.
Mix until smooth and add milk.
Cook until smooth. Alternate 1 layer of cabbage, cheese and white sauce in greased casserole dish until all used.
Melt 4 teaspoons margarine; add to bread crumbs and top.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and salt.
Add vanilla. Sift together flour and baking powder; add to the first mixture. Add bananas and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Grease pan before baking.

title: date roll
directions: Put dates and marshmallows into milk to soften.
Add pecans, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and add crumbs.
Roll into a roll in graham crumbs.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: tomato-zucchini tart
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Core and slice tomatoes 1/4-inch; set aside.
Lightly coat the bottom of a jelly roll or roasting pan with olive oil.
Slice zucchini 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange in oiled pan in single layer.
Brush with 1/2 cup olive oil.
Bake until barely tender, about 3 minutes.
Remove pan from oven; set aside. In large skillet, heat 3 tablespoons olive oil until hot.
Add onions; cook and stir for 5 minutes.
Mix in garlic and sugar; cook and stir over low heat until onions are very soft, but not browned, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Lightly coat the bottom of an 11 x 14-inch jelly roll pan with olive oil. Unroll pizza dough; place in pan and using fingertips, press evenly onto bottom and sides.
Spread cooled onion mixture over dough. Arrange tomato slices over onions, overlapping slightly.
Tuck zucchini slices in between tomatoes.
Scatter olives on top. Combine oregano, thyme, black pepper and salt with 2 tablespoons olive oil; drizzle over vegetables.
Bake until crust is golden, about 25 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream apple cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients in large bowl.
With electric mixer, beat in alternately the eggs and sour cream.
Fold in chopped apples and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° to 350° in large greased pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Cake is done when no imprint remains when touched lightly with finger tip.

title: poor folks biscuits
directions: Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and broth together.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, place half (spread) of Stove Top dressing.
Pour 3/4 cup broth mixture over dressing.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook cake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove and cool.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix all ingredients, holding back 1/4 cup pecans.
Spray ring with Pam and put 1/4 cup pecans in bottom.
Press cheese mixture in mold and refrigerate.
Can place small bowl of strawberry jam or olives in center of ring when serving.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt, egg, Crisco and vinegar together.
Then add water.
Roll on floured board.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter spread
directions: Combine peanut butter and margarine, stirring until smooth. Stir in corn syrup.
Mix well.
Use on rice cakes, toast or waffles.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and take it off bones.
Reserve 3 cups broth. Put chicken in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Melt margarine and pour over chicken.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix meal, soda and salt.
Beat eggs slightly and add to buttermilk; then stir into dry ingredients.
Add bacon fat; stir in corn.
Mix cheese, garlic, onion and peppers.
Add to meal mixture.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Can be mixed ahead and refrigerated overnight.
Cover with foil while refrigerated.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add egg, milk and shortening.
Stir lightly.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook broccoli just under tender. Heat soup with milk and stir in shrimp. Arrange layers of broccoli, soup mixture and cheese in baking dish. Sprinkle with crumbs and spoon melted butter over top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown ground round beef thoroughly with seasonings (salt, pepper, onion, etc.).
Drain thoroughly in colander to remove fat. Wash with hot tap water in colander; drain.
Proceed with whatever recipe that uses browned ground beef:
chili, Sloppy Joes, etc.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together and make out by hand, or roll out and cut.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Add the flour to the Crisco and salt.
Use pie blender or 2 knives to cut in small pieces.
Add the liquid, mix together and form into a ball.
Divide dough into 4 or 5 balls.
Wrap separately and freeze until needed.
Freezes very well.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Roll in paprika or nuts. Return to refrigerator until ready to use.

title: fat-free pizza
directions: Slice French bread into 1-inch slices. Spread pizza sauce onto bread. Lightly spread cheese. Bake until cheese is melted.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Pour off grease.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: pina colada dip
directions: Mix well.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: meat patties
directions: Liquify onion, eggs, mayo and sugar in blender.
Mix this with all other ingredients.
Form into a large patties.
Roll in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in 3 tablespoons shortening in fry pan.
Then add 3 cups hot water and 3 bouillon cubes. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes until done.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine 8 cups water and sugar; boil 15 minutes and let cool. Add all other ingredients except ginger ale.
Mix thoroughly and freeze.
Take out of freezer 2 hours before serving. Add ginger ale at serving time.
No extra ice needed.
Serves 50.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and spoon off fat.
Stir in soups, water, mixed vegetables, and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into 3 quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into quarters.
Remove dish from oven and stir.
Arrange biscuit quarters around the edge, on top of the hot beef mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Mix butter and flour together to thick consistency.
Set aside.
In a pot, bring water to a boil.
Add chicken base; dissolve.
Add butter and flour mixture.
Lower heat and let simmer.
Add remaining ingredients; let simmer for a long, long time.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and sugar.
Stir well.
Pat into an ungreased pizza pan and bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Whip cream cheese, confectioners sugar and whip topping mix together.
Spread on cooled crust.
Drain fruit.
Place in the middle of the pizza. Spread the fruit until it comes within 2 inches from the edge of the pizza pan.
Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together well.
Bake in two greased loaf pans for 45 to 60 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: blueberry bran muffins(low-fat, low cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, bran and baking soda. Add all ingredients, except blueberries; stir to moisten.
Gently fold in blueberries.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs together.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice together.
After sifting together, add to first mixture.
Chop or grate apples and add to mixture. Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and drain well.
Beat eggs; stir in mayonnaise, celery soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Fold into cooked broccoli.
Put in casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes.
Use bread crumbs or grated cheese for topping.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes a larger cake.
Can be baked in 3 (8-inch) square pans or a long pan. Bake about 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Good!

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Use whole strawberries with stems attached and dip halfway down into melted bittersweet chocolate.
Place on wax paper-lined baking sheets and refrigerate at least one hour and up to 24 hours.

title: butner's cream pies
directions: Soak raisins in warm water and put in colander to drain (or may use 3/4 cup crushed pineapple or 2 bananas for a fruit cream pie).

title: italian chicken(this main dish is low in fat and sodium.)
directions: Brown chicken in hot frying pan.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and pour the mixture over chicken.
Heat the mixture until it boils, then
reduce the heat, cover and cook over low heat until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Do not drain corn; mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pear bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Combine oil, eggs, sugar, pears and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Spoon into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: new fashioned baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients into casserole.
Bake in moderate oven about 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated and onions and bacon are cooked.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in deep casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until brown at 350°.
Serves 12. Compote-relish type.

title: chocolate cake pie
directions: Combine and pack into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: rosedale pasta salad
directions: In jar, combine oil, juice and spices; shake well.
Cook rotini; toss with dressing.
Cool.
Stir-fry broccoli and red pepper in oil 5 minutes or until just crisp.
Add peas; cook 1 minute.
Cover, cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Cool.
Toss with tomatoes and parsley.
Chill well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Will also need a 9-inch spring-form pan buttered and coated with 1/4 cup graham cracker crumbs.

title: pfeffernuesse
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and molasses.
Add egg.
Add dry ingredients and oil of anise.
Mix until well blended.
Chill at least one hour, roll the size of a lead pencil, slice.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple ice cream topping
directions: In a 6 - 8 qt. sauce pan, heat lemon juice for 1 minute over medium - high heat.

Add water, apples, sugar, and cinnamon. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly for 3 minutes. Immediately fill hot pint jars, leaving 1/4 inch head space. Carefully run a non - metallic utensil down inside of jars to remove trapped air bubbles.
Wipe jar tops and threads clean. Place hot lids on jars and screw bands on firmly.
Process in boiling water canner for 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding and milk.
Beat until thick.
Fold in sour cream and Cool
Whip by hand.
Make layers of bananas, wafers and pudding.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fabulous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together and put in fridge for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Put on tinfoil to cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix ingredients together.
Roll into balls. Brown on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: joann's peach cobbler
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients with pastry blender.
Put peaches in the bottom of pan.
Sprinkle mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: watermelon supreme
directions: Cut top
third lengthwise from watermelon.
Scoop balls from watermelon.
Scoop remaining pulp from watermelon to form shell. Drain shell.
Cut
thin
slice from bottom of shell to keep it from
tipping.
Scoop
melon balls from cantaloupe and honeydew melon.
Remove
rind
and core from pineapple and cut fruit
into bite
size
pieces.
Just
before
serving
slice peaches.
Mix all fruit in large bowl; drizzle with Honey-Wine Sauce.
Spoon fruit into watermelon shell.
Serve immediately. Makes 20 servings; 80 calories per serving.

title: california cole slaw
directions: Slice the green onions thinly.
Toast the sunflower seed nuts on a cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350° in oven.
Mix cabbage, onions, almonds and sunflower seed nuts together.

title: chicken rice
directions: Mix first five
ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 15 inch casserole dish.
Put chicken thighs on top of rice mixture.
Baste with margarine, sprinkle with lemon pepper, then paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours covered with foil.
Remove foil last 15 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into baking pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: good stuff-fruit dessert
directions: In a pretty glass bowl, break up angel food cake in small pieces.
Mix together sour cream, milk, sugar and Cool Whip and pour over cake pieces and toss until well coated.
Top with a can of fruit pie filling of your choice.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes in bowl.
Add eggs, 1/2 cup butter, cinnamon and sugar; mix well.
Dissolve cornstarch in milk in small bowl.
Add to sweet potatoes; mix well.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: apple pan dowdy
directions: Line a casserole with pie crust.
Mix sugar, spices and salt and sprinkle over apples.
Fill casserole with apples.
Add molasses, butter and water.
Cover with punctured pie crust.
Tuck edges together.
Press to sides of casserole.

title: grillades and grits
directions: Trim all fat from meat.
Cut into serving pieces and pound with mallet.
Rub salt, pepper and garlic into meat on both sides. Then, rub in flour.
In heavy pan, melt shortening over medium heat and brown grillades (meat) on both sides.
Lower heat and add onion, tomato and 1 cup water.
Bring to simmer, cover loosely and cook over low heat for about 30 minutes, turning meat every 10 minutes.
If too thick, add water a little at a time.
Remove to platter and place in 200° oven to keep warm.
Prepare grits according to package directions.
Reheat gravy and serve to put on grits or top grits with butter.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix water, sugar and Jell-O until dissolved.
Add cranberries, sour cream and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set; spray mold with Pam for easy removal of Jell-O.

title: toffee candy
directions: Chop almonds or pecans and spread onto a small cooking sheet (enough to cover about a 10 x 12-inch cookie sheet).
If using almonds, brown in oven.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Leave pineapple in can. Prepare 1 package jello, using half the water.
Pour jello into can of pineapple.
Chill until set.
Run a little hot water on can to remove jello or cut out bottom of can and push jello through. Cut between slices and serve.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine cider, orange juice, lemon juice, sugar, 3 cinnamon sticks, cloves and nutmeg in a heavy saucepan.
Heat over medium heat to boiling.
Keep on stove over low heat.
Strain.
Serve with a cinnamon stick in mugs.

title: buttermilk puffs
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add wet ingredients gently with a fork.
Drop by teaspoon into deep fat at 375°.
Roll in powdered or granulated sugar.
Do not make too large or they won't cook through.
When removing from fat, drain on brown grocery bag.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump undrained pineapple into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread evenly.
Dump the pie filling over pineapple; spread evenly.
Dump the dry cake mix onto the cherry layer.
Spread the pecans and coconut evenly over the dry cake mix.
Place the slices of butter over top.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Serve warm or cooled.
Delicious to serve warm with vanilla ice cream on top.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown beef top round.
Mix flour, pepper, dry mustard, chopped onion, soup and sour cream.
Mix noodles, beef and mixture.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour milk almost to top (just so you can see it).
Cut up cheese and put on top (Velveeta).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese melts and starts to brown.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook to boiling, then boil for 10 minutes.
Wash jars and pour hot water in them just before you fill with picante sauce so they will be hot.
Boil lids 2 to 3 minutes. Fill jars to about 1/2-inch from top.
Wipe all juice from edges of jar.
Tighten lids.
Lids will seal in approximately 2 hours.
Enjoy!!

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Tear bread in small pieces, then pour liquid over bread.
Sprinkle with nutmeg on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: alverda's date hills
directions: Beat the egg whites until very stiff.
Add the sugar very slowly, beating well.
Mix the walnuts and dates together and add to the egg mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
You judge the time, but do not overbake.

title: whole-wheat scones
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into a mixing bowl.
Cut in lard until mixture resembles coarse meal or crumbs.
Make a hollow in the center.
Beat eggs slightly; combine with milk.
Stir into the hollow in flour mixture with fork to moisten all ingredients.
Avoid overmixing.
Turn onto floured board; knead lightly 5 or 6 times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on an ungreased griddle or skillet preheated over medium heat.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk with mixer.
Add crumbled Oreo cookies.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer with Cool Whip.
Spread nuts on top.
Evenly cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: butter beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Work together with hands and make small balls.
Chill overnight. With a toothpick,
dip
the
balls into 1/2 stick of paraffin and 2 (12 ounce) bags of
chocolate chips that have been melted together.
Set in cool place until chocolate coating has hardened.

title: gravy for shrimp balls
directions: Make a roux with flour and oil.
Saute onion and bell pepper in roux.
Add water and remaining ingredients.
Cook 2 hours on low heat.
Serves 4.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Mix all together well.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Right before cooking, mix 1/2 can of oriental noodles (5 ounce) with casserole and put the rest on top.
Cook in oven at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: amy's chocolate cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix as directed.
After cake is cooled, ice.

title: creamed hash browns
directions: Thaw hash browns in a 3-quart casserole for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream, soup, onions, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix flakes with melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Heat on Full power for 15 minutes.

title: grandma glahn's apple crunch
directions: Put apples in greased baking dish. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over and dot with the butter.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt margarine and place in rectangular casserole dish.
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top of margarine.
Drain asparagus and place in casserole dish.
Drain artichoke hearts and cut in half and place in between asparagus spears.
Slice hard-boiled eggs over asparagus and artichoke hearts.
Place sliced Swiss cheese on top.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 can of water and pour on top of Swiss cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: snapped-up green beans
directions: In 1-quart casserole dish, combine bacon and onion.
Cover; microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Add beans and remaining ingredients. Re-cover.
Microwave on High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes more, until beans are heated, stirring after half the time.

title: italian chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Place the chicken breasts in baking pan and cover with the Italian dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until they test done.

title: taco salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces; add cooked and drained ground beef.
Add chopped onion, drained beans, cheese and chips.
Toss and add Italian dressing.

title: goofy cake
directions: Melt margarine in large 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Mix 2 eggs with cake mix and sprinkle over butter in pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar; pour this over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Eat and enjoy.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all together in blender.
Pour into greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.
Recipe may be halved.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes.
Strain juice of lemon and oranges and add with the syrup to grape juice and tea.
Chill for several hours.
Add ginger ale, then pour over ice cubes and garnish with mint leaves and slices of strawberries or cherries.

title: white spaghetti
directions: Saute vegetables.
Add 1 block of Velveeta cheese and chicken. Add seasonings.
Mix well with 1 package cooked spaghetti.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pecans and coconut on bottom. Mix cake per instructions and pour into pan.
Melt together cream cheese, sugar and butter and pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and green pepper.
Drain fat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: beany weany burger biscuit pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Separate dough into biscuits and arrange around sides and bottom of 9 x 14-inch pan. Press dough to form crust. In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Stir in beans, brown sugar, hot dogs and syrup. Simmer for 5 minutes over low heat until slightly thickened. Spoon mixture over prepared crust. Bake at 400° for 12 to 16 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven and bake 3 to 4 minutes more until cheese melts. Allow to cool 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown first five ingredients.
Add tomatoes and water.
Simmer two hours, adding water as necessary, seasoning to taste.

title: scrambled eggs and crab(serves 6)
directions: Fry bacon until lightly brown.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Combine eggs and milk, seasoning and crabmeat.
Add to onion mixture.
Cook until eggs are firm, stirring occasionally.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well together. Bake in a loaf pan at 300° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as package states.
Add cream cheese; beat together.
Add maraschino juice and cut-up maraschino cherries. Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Keep adding miniature marshmallows until thick.
Set in refrigerator to chill 1 or 2 days before using.

title: everyone's favorite casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt and pepper; drain. Add macaroni, tomatoes, 1 1/2 cups cheese and sugar. Mix well and place in lightly buttered casserole. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tony's punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with water and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Adjust ingredients to taste.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except oil.
With water moistened hands, shape in 8 patties, using 1/4 cup mixture for each.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add patties and cook about 3 minutes per side, until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kahlua cheesecake(crustless)
directions: Combine cottage cheese and cream cheese in large bowl of electric mixer. Beat at high speed until creamed. Gradually add sugar. Cream well after each addition. In separate bowl, beat eggs, cornstarch, flour and vanilla together. Stir sour cream and butter into egg mixture. Blend cheese and egg mixtures together. Pour into a well-greased 10-inch spring-form pan. Mix cocoa with Kahlua; swirl into batter. Bake at 350° for 70 minutes. Turn off oven; cool in oven 1 hour without opening door. Chill cake until firm. Serves 10 to 12.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 325` for 30 minutes.
Mix cracker crumbs and butter, sprinkle over casserole.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter 9 x 11-inch dish.
Butter sides of heavy pan (such as pressure cooker).
Combine sugars, Carnation cream, milk and butter.
Heat, stirring (wooden spoon) constantly, until mixture boils.
Cook to soft ball stage.
(Test for soft ball stage is, into 1 cup of cold water, drop a 1/2 teaspoon of hot mix; if it can be made into a ball, candy mix is ready.)
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Set pan in cold water and beat until it loses its glossy look.
Pour into buttered dish (or pan).
Let cool and cut into squares before candy gets cold.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in saute pan. When done, cube. Saute onions, green or red peppers, mushrooms and butter. Stir in soups, Velveeta, Ro-Tel tomatoes and chopped chicken. Boil spaghetti until al dente; drain. Combine spaghetti and chicken soup and cheese mixture together. Place in 11 x 13 casserole dish and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dr. ziment's garlic chicken soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a stockpot; bring to a boil and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Strain through a sieve, discard bay leaf and puree solids in a blender or food processor. Return broth and puree to the pot.
Stir well and reheat if necessary.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips and dust with flour and pepper. In a large skillet, brown steak in oleo or butter; add mushrooms, onion and garlic and brown lightly.
Stir in broth; cover and cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Gradually stir in sour cream and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: 1930 tomato soup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Combine all dry ingredients.
Add to this shortening and 1/2 can of soup.
Beat well and add remaining soup and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in floured raisins and nuts to mixture.
Blend well. Pour into pans.
Bake about 1 hour.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in hot water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in cranberry sauce, celery and chopped nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 10-inch pie plate with nonstick spray.
Cook turkey and onion.
Stir in seasoning; mix.
Cook until blended.
Spread in plate; top with green chiles.
Beat together milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture in pie plate.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, milk and butter; boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Put oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla in and beat until cool.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.

title: coal miner's cake
directions: Bake cake according to package.
In saucepan, warm mixture of sugar, margarine and evaporated milk over low heat.
Bring to a low boil for a minute.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour over cake.

title: fresh cranberry orange sauce
directions: Wash and pick cranberries.
Place in a saucepan with sugar, orange juice and salt.
Cover and bring to boiling point.
Cook only until skins pop, 6 to 8 minutes.
Chill and serve with turkey, pork, ham or chicken.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring
the butter and water to boiling point.
Sift the flour and
salt together.
Add the flour all at once and beat vigorously until
mixture
is
thick and smooth.
Remove from fire.
Add beaten
eggs
gradually
to
the
mixture, beating thoroughly after
each
addition and until smooth.
Drop on a greased baking sheet or muffin pan about 2 inches apart.
Bake in	a
very
hot oven (475°) for about 10 minutes, then reduce heat slightly for about 25 minutes longer or until muffins are a light brown.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, cocoa, soda and salt together several times, then add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
After mixed thoroughly, add boiling water and beat well.
Then add vanilla.
Mixture will be very thin.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Brown, drain and crumble sausage.
Combine all ingredients. Mix well (with hands).
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.
Can reheat in microwave.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Finely chop first 5 ingredients in food processor.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until thick.
Hot pack (remove bay leaves before canning).

title: french bread
directions: Mix warm water and yeast in food processor.
Add salt and oil; add a little flour at a time.
Keep adding flour, 1/4 cup at a time until dough comes away from bowl.
Should be able to handle dough without sticking to fingers.
Knead dough on floured surface for 30 seconds.
Place in greased bowl and cover for 20 minutes. Remove and knead for 30 seconds more.
Place in bowl and cover for another 20 minutes.
Remove from bowl and place on floured surface.
Push out air bubbles, then roll dough out into oblong shape.
Brush dough with some water.
Roll dough up like a carpet. Turn ends under.
Sprinkle cornmeal on cookie sheet.
Place loaf on sheet.
Slash along top of bread.
Cover; let rise for 30 minutes.
Brush top of bread with water.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
Bread sounds hollow if tapped on bottom when done.

title: st. patrick's day dessert
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust and chill. Dissolve lime jello, creme de menthe and hot water. Add remaining ingredients. Chill.

title: smoked brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over meat.
Place brisket in pan with tight fitting lid or foil.
Do not open until done.
Bake for 4 to 6 hours at 275°.
If using smoker, wrap brisket in heavy foil and cook over grill 4 to 6 hours.
This is good!

title: caramel sauce
directions: Boil all ingredients, except milk and butter, to soft ball stage.
Add butter.
When cool add evaporated milk.
Beat well until light colored.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: sour cream chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish, skin side up.
Combine soup, mushrooms and sour cream; mix well and pour over chicken.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Cream margarine, add sugar.
Beat at medium speed on mixer. Add eggs, beat well.
Stir in sweet potatoes.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Spoon in greased muffin caps, filling 2/3 full.
Combine 2 Tbsp. sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 - 25 minutes.

title: cranberry muffins(1 dozen)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar; cream again.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Stir in cranberries.
Fill twelve greased muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: picante dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain picante sauce.
Using the pulp, whip the cream cheese with pulp until completely mixed.
A little juice can be used if the cream cheese is too hard.

title: the brown cow
directions: Peel and slice bananas; beat until smooth in blender.
Add syrup, 1/2 cup milk and vanilla; mix well and add remaining milk. Pour into glasses and top each with scoop of ice cream.

title: picnic fruit punch
directions: Combine the juices in a large container and refrigerate. Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and orange slices.

title: easy supper
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
In a small casserole dish put can of Spaghetti O's.
Add hamburger.
Stir and top with crushed chips. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: country chicken soup
directions: Chop and saute onion and margarine; add noodle soup, broth, corn, milk and pepper.
Put all in blender for few minutes, then add chicken.
Heat to boiling point but do not boil; sprinkle on parsley and serve hot.

title: grams molasses cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, molasses and salt mixing well.
Add flour, raisins and pecans.

title: tuna stuffed tomato salad
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Dice and add eggs.
Add mustard, Miracle Whip, relish and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well. With a sharp knife, remove stem end of tomatoes and cut from the top to within 1/2-inch of bottom, creating 6-inch petals.
Place lettuce leaves on small plates; center with tomato.
Fill with tuna salad.
Garnish with stuffed olives.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in bowl; set aside.
Combine vinegar, water, peppercorns, bay leaves, cloves, salt and pepper in a saucepan. Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Pour mixture over meat; cool.
Cover tightly and put in refrigerator.
Marinate for five days; turn meat once a day.
Remove meat from marinade and drain thoroughly.
Strain and reserve juice.
Using a Dutch oven, brown; add 1 cup marinade, carrots and onions.
Bring rapidly to a boil; cover tightly and simmer about 2 hours, or until tender. Remove meat and add gingersnaps and sugar into liquid in Dutch oven.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
This makes delicious gravy.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave 4 minutes on High.
Stir and microwave 4 more minutes on High. Add butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Add soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Cool. Break into small pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: veggie dip
directions: Blend all but mayonnaise, then fold in mayonnaise and chill.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in pot you will use to make soup in.
Saute vegetables until soft.
Add flour and cornstarch and cook until bubbly.
Add stock and milk and make a smooth sauce.
Add soda and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with parsley before serving if desired.
Use a large pot; will foam after soda is added.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in skillet. Pour mixture of flour, sugar, milk and vanilla into center of butter. Pour peaches and some of the juice into middle of skillet (cast-iron works great). Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon and bake at 350° until golden brown (about 1 hour).

title: barbecue crock-pot
directions: Mix catsup, beer and onion soup mix.
Pour over meat.
(May also add barbecue sauce.)
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or until meat can be shredded.

title: banana split pie
directions: Press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.

title: squash pickles
directions: Soak squash in 3-quarts water with salt for 1 hour.
Pour off brine.
Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard and celery seed and bring to a boil.
Add all vegetables and bring back to a boil but do not cook!
Pack in hot jars and seal.
Yields 8 pints.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown ground beef and onion until onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, corn, green beans, carrot, bouillon, parsley, basil, oregano and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: apple-cranberry salad
directions: For dressing, in a screw top jar, combine oil, cider or juice, vinegar, cinnamon and cloves.
Cover and shake well to mix.
Chill until needed.
If using cranberries, toss berries with 2 tablespoons of the sugar; let stand for 15 minutes.
Toss with remaining 1 tablespoon sugar for a frosted look.
For grapes, which are sweeter, omit the sugar.
Arrange greens on 4 salad plates.
Top with apple slices.
Shake dressing; pour over salads. Top with cranberries or grapes.
Makes 4 to 6 side dish servings.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add butter, milk and vanilla. Mix in rice and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Use regular round glass baking dish.
Can also add raisins, if desired.

title: herb-spinach-cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Pierce pie shell with fork.
Bake until pale gold.
Cool.
Reduce oven to 350°.

title: easy yellow cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on box.
While cake is hot, punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour Eagle Brand milk all over, then when cake cools, spread Cool Whip on top.
Add nuts, coconut or fruit, if desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, salt and milk.
Stir until mixed.
Then, without stirring, cook to 234° or until mixture forms soft ball stage in cold water.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat; pour into buttered pan.

title: lucy's cake
directions: Bake angel food cake according to package directions, cool. Dissolve gelatin in 4 Tbsp. cold water, add hot water and stir until dissolved - add pineapple, sugar, lemon juice - put in refrigerator to set or thicken.

Whip 2 envelopes dream whip with 1 cup sweet milk and 1/2 tsp. vanilla - add this to the gelatin mixture - break up angel food cake in large pan - add the gelatin mixture, nuts and cherries, mix thoroughly.
Grease tub pan - spoon mixture into pan and press down.
Chill overnight - ice with 1 package dream whip and 1/2 cup milk.
Spread with coconut and cherries.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter; add beef and cook in remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Add soup, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Lower heat and add sour cream when mixture no longer boils.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Bake biscuits according to package directions.
Meanwhile, break sausage into chunks in a medium skillet.
Add sage and brown over medium heat.
Add flour and stir to coat meat and soak up the oils.
Season with salt and pepper.
Over low heat, slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking and stirring until thickened.
Serve immediately over warm biscuits.

title: tuna shell salad
directions: Use enough of each for your taste.
Serve on lettuce.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and fry together with chopped onion; drain off part of the grease.
Add to beans and mix all the remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Place in a large casserole with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add cheese last 30 minutes.

title: saltless seasoning salt
directions: Mix all together and put into shaker.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Mix the water with 1 cup of tomato juice; heat until boiling. Dissolve in this the jello; gently stir.
Now add the V-8, tomato juice, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Chill until it starts to jell.
Then add, if desired, the chopped vegetables.

title: cajun corn bread
directions: Heat 1/4 cup cooking oil in iron skillet in 400° oven.
While oil is heating, stir together in mixing bowl all ingredients, except Cheddar cheese.
Pour half of batter into heated skillet and top with 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Pour remaining batter on top and sprinkle on other 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 or 45 minutes, until lightly browned on top.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Boil the chicken.
When chicken is finished boiling, take it out of boiler and season it.
Also put the cut up green onions on it, garlic salt, black pepper and salt.
Cut the chicken open about an inch.
Put the corn bread stuffing inside, then put the barbecue sauce on it.
Put in the oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Drain pineapple; mix jello in bowl.
Add sugar.
Dissolve in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Add pineapple juice and all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Chill.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix everything and place in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.
Marshmallows can be put on top of pies the last few minutes of baking.

title: great pasta salad
directions: Mix everything together and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: buttered rice and green peppers
directions: Wash and soak rice.
Place in shallow pan.
Add water and salt.
Let stand, covered, on stove over low heat, for 15 minutes. Add chopped peppers and melted butter to the hot rice.
Toss lightly with fork and add parsley.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Place by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake until set. Cookies should be soft when cool.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Drain liquids.
Mix lightly.
Add celery, chopped onion and green pepper.
Marinate overnight in mixture of remaining ingredients.

title: egg custard pie *
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Add salt, vanilla, sifted flour and chopped pecans.
Mix well. Chill dough for 2 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
While cookies are still warm, roll in powdered sugar. Keep in airtight container.

title: texas style chili
directions: Cut beef for stew into 1/2-inch cubes.
In 8-quart Dutch oven, heat oil, cooking 1/3 of meat at a time.
Remove meat; set aside. Reserve 1/2 cup onion.
Add green peppers and onions to drippings. Cook 10 minutes.
Return meat, add tomatoes and their liquid, tomato paste, chili powder, sugar, salt, oregano, pepper and 2 cups water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce to low heat.
Cover, simmer 1 1/2 hours.
When meat is tender, the chili is done.
Pass reserved onions around to guests to sprinkle over the chili.

title: light 'n fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water 3 minutes. Add ice cubes and stir until thickened, about 3 minutes. Remove ice cubes. Blend in Cool Whip until smooth. Fold in fruit.
Spoon into crust. Chill 2 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1/2 quart strawberries with potato masher or fork.
Add water, sugar and cornstarch; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in butter or margarine.
Quickly pour glaze over remaining strawberries arranged in precooked pie shell. Refrigerate for approximately 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: fresh berry fruit dip
directions: Mix marshmallow cream and cream cheese; mix until well blended.
Add flavoring and 1/2 cup pureed strawberries.
Mix again.
Garnish dip with halved strawberries and toothpicks.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Crumble Doritos into greased casserole dish.

Spread chicken over Doritos and top with chopped onion. Mix soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes together and pour over chip mixture. Top with grated cheese and bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until well heated and cheese is melted.

title: fork cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, dry ingredients, milk and raisins.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon; press down with floured fork.
Bake for about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pat's potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in baking dish.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add onions and water; cook 20 minutes.
Add chili sauce, tomato paste and water. Then add all spices and simmer for 1 hour.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons of the flour with the blueberries.
Mix butter and sugar together, add eggs one at a time beating after each addition.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Add to butter and sugar mixture alternately with the milk starting with and ending with the flour.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Add blueberries and mix with spoon.
Pour into a 9 x 9 inch square pan - well greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well and toss with oil.
In large bowl, layer lettuce, pasta, Miracle Whip, peas, onion rings separated, cheese and crumbled bacon.
Cover; chill thoroughly, overnight.

title: tuna noodle salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and let cool before adding all the other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: salmon, shrimp or crab ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
Chill and then cover with shrimp sauce.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Put browned chicken on top.
Add mushrooms and soup; top with cheese, then bread crumbs.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll biscuits thin and slice apples.
Put apples, cinnamon and sugar (about 1/2 teaspoon) in the biscuits; pull together and pinch biscuits at top.
Put in a long dish.
Bring to boil 1 1/2 cups sugar, water and butter.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over dumplings.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Beat whole egg in deep bowl at high speed of electric mixer until stiff and pale yellow. Add lemon juice and oil by dribbles (very slowly). Continue beating constantly until it reaches desired consistency. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Store in refrigerator. Super good on fresh tomatoes.

title: chili con carne
directions: If using chili beans, soak overnight.
Cook in boiling, salted water until tender.
Brown onion, green pepper, and meat in hot fat.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 2 hours, adding water if necessary.
Add beans, heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: grammaws meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray pan with cooking spray.
Beat eggs.
Add 57 sauce, brown sugar and ketchup, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups cornflake crumbs; mix well.
Add hamburger to ketchup mixture and mix it up well.
(Grammaw says this must be done with your hands.)
Pour into pan and shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon souffle
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar; add lemon juice and lemon rind slowly until blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry with cream of tartar.
Beat whipping cream until peaks form but not stiff.
Add whipped cream to yolk mixture.
Put gelatine into water and let soften for a few minutes.
Heat until liquid, then cool slightly.
Mix gelatine into cream-egg mixture; stir until thickened.
Add beaten egg whites and fold gently.
Chill until firm. Serve with raspberry sauce.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients together in a bowl.
Add the oil, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add the apples and chopped nuts; mix. Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with the butterscotch chips.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: praline apple bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat together sugar, sour cream, eggs and vanilla on low speed with an electric mixer until combined. Then beat on medium speed for two minutes.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt, add to sour cream mixture, beat on low speed until combined.
Stir in apple and 1/2 cup of the pecans. Turn into a greased 9x5x3 inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans and press lightly into batter.
Bake at 350 for 55-60 minutes (test with toothpick).
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes. In a small pan combine butter and brown sugar.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and boil gently for one minute.
Remove bread from pan and drizzle with brown sugar mixture.
Cool.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes in the skins.
Cool, peel and then shred coarsely.
Mix in a saucepan over low heat the cheese and 1/4 cup butter, stirring until almost melted.
Remove from heat; blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in the potatoes.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot the top with the leftover butter, then bake, uncovered, at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ground turkey mix
directions: Combine the ground turkey with the bread crumbs, eggs, onion, milk, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Mix lightly, just until blended.
Divide the mixture into thirds; proceed with Scandinavian Meatballs or your favorite recipes.
Makes 2 (6 serving) recipes.

title: no-bake fudge cookies
directions: Mix together cocoa, margarine, sugar and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Store until thoroughly coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: onion cornbread casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender; remove from heat.
Add sour cream and 1/2 cup of cheese; set aside.
Stir together cornmeal, sugar and dill weed.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Mix sour cream, water and eggs.
Add cake mix and stir until batter is lumpy.
Spread in a greased and floured jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).
Drop pie filling by spoonfuls over batter. Bake until cake springs back, 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with almond.
Drizzle with a powdered sugar glaze.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Combine water, sugar and salt.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 2 minutes only.
Place marshmallow cream in large bowl and pour hot syrup into marshmallow.
Stir until candy loses its gloss.
Add nuts.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken; debone.
Mix with other ingredients except stuffing.
Mix stuffing by instructions on bag.
Chicken broth may be used instead of water when mixing stuffing.
Crumble half of stuffing in bottom of pan.
Pour everything else in, then crumble rest of stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onion with water; boil until done.
Add slices of cheese to thicken.
Soup may be added for extra flavor.

title: popovers
directions: Lightly grease popover pans.
In medium size bowl with rotary mixer, beat eggs and milk with oil until well combined.
Sift flour with salt over egg mixture until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan, filling about 1/2 full.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 400° until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: seven-layer wow bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and condensed milk in prepared pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into squares.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Beat sugar and milk into cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in coconut.
Fold mixture into Cool Whip topping and almond extract. Spoon into pie crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Let stand at room temperature about 15 minutes before cutting.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: pesto by bev(for pasta, dipping sauce or pizza topping)
directions: In a food processor, combine garlic and basil. Add cheese and process until smooth. Add nuts and process until smooth. Drizzle oil in as processing until mixture smoothes out.
Pack in jars almost to the top, pushing out bubbles of air from bottom and sides.
Add olive oil to seal top from oxygen.
Cover with lid.

title: potluck casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown meat and onions together.
Add beans, macaroni and spices.
Pour on sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian eggs
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour.
When well blended, stir tomatoes, celery, onions and cheese into this.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add salt and 1/3 teaspoon paprika.
Turn into buttered casserole, sprinkled with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: garlic bread pizza
directions: Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Divide ingredients equally on each side. Bake in preheated 425° oven 10 to 12 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice. Mix dry jello with cottage cheese. Add drained pineapple and drained oranges. Add 1 tablespoon pineapple juice, mixing well. Fold Cool Whip into mixture. Chill in a mold or pan (may be glass) at least 2 hours before serving.

title: baked apple delight
directions: Peel, core, and slice thin 4 apples.
In a greased 1 to 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer about 1/3 of the slices.
Sprinkle with about a tablespoon of sugar and a little cinnamon.
Repeat apple and sugar layers 2 more times.
Cover tightly and bake at 300° about 1 1/2 hours or until very tender.
Keep covered and let cool.
Serve with whipped topping if desired.

title: souper burgers
directions: In skillet brown beef and cook onion until tender.
Stir to separate meat.
Add soup and seasonings.
Heat; stir often. Serve on buns.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: pan buckeyes
directions: Melt powdered sugar, margarine and 1 cup of peanut butter in microwave; put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa; stir until smooth.
Add well beaten eggs, flour, salt and sugar; beat together until smooth. Add nuts and stir again.
Pour into a square pan, sprayed with Pam, and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Layer mini marshmallows over top of hot cake.

title: ranch-parmesan potatoes
directions: Cook cubed potatoes until done. Layer in baking dish the potatoes, Ranch dressing and Parmesan cheese. Make 2 layers. Drizzle melted butter over top. Put in oven for 15 or 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Mash garlic, thyme, oregano and salt and saute in butter in bottom of saucepan. Add milk and bring to a boil; remove from heat and add cheese. Set aside to cool.
Boil macaroni in salt water until just tender. Add to milk-cheese sauce after 3 eggs have been mixed into sauce until blended.
Pour into a greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown. Serves 6.

title: corn fritters
directions: Using 2 mixing bowls, separate egg yolk in one bowl and egg white in the other bowl.
Add to egg yolk the corn, flour, salt and water.
Mix thoroughly.
(Mixture should be fairly thick.) Whisk the egg white into a thick froth and add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Make about 4 fritters; spoon into an oiled frypan and cook until brown on both sides.

title: raw tomato catsup
directions: Mix together tomatoes, onions and salt.
Place in a cheesecloth or jelly bag.
Hang to drain overnight.

title: root beer
directions: Pour sugar in large, clean container.
Pour extract over sugar.
Crumble yeast into 8 ounces of warm water (comfortable to inside of wrist).
Set aside for 5 minutes.
Fill container half full with water to dissolve sugar.
Add root beer extract and yeast mixture; stir very good.
Add additional water to container. Fill clean quart bottles 1 inch from top.
Cap tightly.

title: transparent pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in uncooked pie crust in slow oven until browned.
May use egg whites for meringue, adding 2 tablespoons sugar to each egg white.
Cook meringue until browned.

title: linguine parmesan
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Add other ingredients.

title: corn and sausage casserole
directions: Combine corn, green peppers and onions.
Place half of the mixture in bottom of a 10 x 6 x 2-inch buttered baking dish. Sprinkle crackers over corn. Add remaining corn.
Top with 3/4 cup broken crackers.
Mix milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over corn mixture.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Brown the sausage links. Serve on top of baked corn.

title: sunday steak
directions: Cover steak with mustard and sprinkle with onion soup.
Cover with slices of bacon.
Roll and place in foil.
Add mushroom soup and bring foil up and close tightly.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour or until tender.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Boil potatoes 10 minutes in water with salt to taste.
While potatoes cook, saute onion in oleo until tender.
Mix Cheez Whiz and sour cream and add to onion.
Drain potatoes and place in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish and pour the cheese mixture over them.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 more minutes.

title: rhubarb cake dessert
directions: Crumb together butter, 2 cups flour and 2 teaspoons sugar. Press into cake pan.
Mix rhubarb, egg yolks, 2 cups sugar, 4 teaspoons flour, cream or milk and salt.
Pour on crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Bring water and cube to a boil.
Add 1/2 stick oleo and soup. Heat to boil.
Pour over rice in 1 3/4-quart casserole dish. Cover with foil.
Put in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and add mushrooms.
Bake for 30 minutes or more.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread cherry
filling	on
bottom of a 7 x 7-inch pan. Add pineapple,	if desired. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit. Add nuts. Place
margarine
in
slices over mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook apples with brown sugar and cinnamon to taste for about 1 hour.
Add apples into pie crust and pour in milk.
Add butter. Cover with crumb topping.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: red beans and rice(serves 6)
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic and saute.
Stir in all spices; add canned beans (or add to prepared dried beans and cook 1 hour uncovered) and heat.
Add sausage (optional) and heat.
Remove bay leaves and stir in parsley.
Serve over oven rice with corn bread.

title: aunt helen's sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add ketchup and mustard.
Pour over undiluted soup and mix in cheese until melted.
Serve over hamburger buns.

title: party balls
directions: Mix all together.
Can make one large ball or best for appetizers, make into 1-inch balls and put toothpick in each one on a platter for serving.

title: ambrosia
directions: Section oranges.
Pour milk and cream into top of a double boiler and heat over boiling water until scalded.
Beat egg yolks in a mixing bowl until light and stir in sugar, flour and salt. Add milk mixture slowly, stirring constantly.
Return to double boiler and cook until thick.
Cool; then add sherry.
Place alternate layers of orange sections, custard and coconut ending with coconut.
Chill thoroughly.

title: mary lou's yummie goodie
directions: First Layer:
Cream together flour, butter, brown sugar and nuts.
Put into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish that has been greased. Cook for 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate dream
directions: Combine flour, margarine and pecans in bowl.
Mix well. Spread evenly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: pull apart coffee cake(monkey bread)
directions: With 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon, mix in a plastic bag.
Cut biscuits into quarters and toss in sugar bag.
Melt oleo, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Drop quartered biscuits into this briefly, then drop into an ungreased Bundt pan or angel food pan.
Sprinkle a few nuts and raisins on each layer. Continue until all are coated.
Pour any remaining sugar mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and turn out onto large plate.
You can put icing, if you wish.

title: steak mardi gras
directions: In large skillet, cook steak in oil to desired doneness, turning once; remove and keep warm.
In same skillet, stir in remaining ingredients; heat until bubbly.
Thinly slice steak diagonally across the grain; spoon sauce over.
Serve with rice, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: red roosters
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze. Remove from freezer about 1/2 hour before serving. Put into a punch bowl and stir to make slush.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake the cake.
Top with crushed pineapple, pudding and Cool Whip, then coconut.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and vanilla; cream well.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Chill.
If necessary, add more flour to prevent stickiness when rolling dough on floured board. Roll to 1/16 to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into circles.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Top each circle with small amount of Raisin Filling.
Top with another circle and press edges to seal.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until delicately browned.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in sugar and Karo syrup.
Bring to a boil, stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Place nuts on a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake at 250° about 1 hour.
Stir them several times.
Cool on wax paper.
Separate and place in tightly covered containers.

title: crab melts
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread mix onto 6 split English muffins. Sprinkle crabmeat on top.
Cut into quarters.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: key lime pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine condensed milk, lime juice and food coloring (color to your own taste).
Pour into crust and chill. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: spiced crust for fruit pie(this is a great crust for a fruit pie.)
directions: Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes. Cover pie with a large pan or lid and then bake 35 to 40 minutes longer in a 350° oven.
When cooled, add whipped cream topping, if desired.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 1 3/4-quart greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and parboil in salt water until tender; drain and mash well.
Add cracker crumbs.
Mix eggs and milk and add to squash.
Add onion, bell pepper, cheese, butter, sugar, salt and pepper. Put in buttered pan and top with more cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mozzarella dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: gooseberry pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and cook until thickens.
Add a pinch of baking soda.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and put on a top crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grape leaves
directions: Combine the meat, uncooked rice, salt, pepper and juice of 4 lemons; mix thoroughly.
Use a 3-quart pot; put aluminum foil on bottom of pan.
Wash vine leaves; separate each one gently.
Snip the stem.
Lay each leaf flat; place a level tablespoon of stuffing on each leaf.
Shape the stuffing in the center; fold sides to the center.
Roll up from larger end and toward tip.
Press together firmly so it will hold its shape.
Place in pan (on top of tinfoil), side by side and close together, in layers, in order to retain shape, until all leaves are used.
Weight down with heat resistant plate.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks one at a time, beating until creamy.
Add flavoring; add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for an hour and 30 minutes.
Glaze with your favorite glaze, if desired.

title: pineapple-pecan loaf bread
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with orange juice concentrate, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in pineapple and pecans.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove and cool on wire rack.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Remove stem and seeds from bell peppers.
Put 1/2 peppers and 1/2 vinegar in blender and puree.
Pour in pot and repeat with other half of peppers and vinegar.
Pour in pot with other peppers and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Add food coloring. Remove from heat and add Certo.
Boil 2 minutes.
Skim and pour into jelly glasses.
Allow glasses to cool before pouring 1/4-inch of paraffin on top.

title: holiday salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and mix with hot water and jello.
Let set and then whip.
Add cottage cheese, nuts and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: In double boiler, mix chocolate chips, milk, butter and salt. Stir until mixture is smooth.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Spread about 2/3 of oatmeal mixture in pan.
Cover with chocolate.
Dot with remaining oatmeal and swirl into chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Tear cauliflower and lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Then add chopped onion, bacon and shredded cheese.
Mix together.

title: soft molasses cookies(sweet cakes)
directions: Add soda to molasses and let foam for 5 minutes.
Cream sugar and
shortening with the salt and spices.
Add to molasses	and soda
mixture.
Add
beaten
egg, water and vinegar. Beat well. Stir in 3 cups flour.
Roll cookies quite thick on a floured board.
Cut with a large cookie cutter.
Score tops with
a
fork and
sprinkle
with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: butter tarts(makes approximately 2 dozen)
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar, vanilla and vinegar.
Mix well. Add melted butter and blend well.
Stir in raisins.
Fill tart 1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes and at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fast fixin fruit n cake(one pan, no bowls)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan until pan is covered on bottom. Put cake mix, eggs and water into pan. Stir with fork or spoon until blended, about 2 minutes.
Scrape sides and batter evenly in pan.
Spoon pie filling onto batter, use a fork or knife to mix pie filling through cake just enough to create a marble effect.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cooled cake may be sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Store cake loosely covered.

title: elsie's oatmeal bread
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Combine boiling water, oats, syrup, shortening and salt.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add yeast and flour (sticky dough).
Cover and let rise, until double.
Knead lightly.
Shape, put into pans lightly greased.
Let rise again. Bake at 350° approximately 35 minutes.

title: chocolate delight (or lemon)
directions: Mix until crumbly and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: italian stuffed meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch baking pan.
Combine ground beef, oats, 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce, onion, Parmesan cheese, egg, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; mix well.
Separate mixture into 2 equal parts.
Shape each into a patty about 2-inches in diameter.

title: baked spanish rice
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper. Crumble and set aside.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings. Saute onions and green peppers in drippings until tender.
Drain tomatoes, reserving juice.
Add enough water to reserved juice to make 1 3/4 cups.
Cut up tomatoes.
Add liquid, tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar and salt to onions and peppers; heat to boiling. Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Remove mixture from heat and stir in rice; pour into casserole.
Cover; bake 35 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Fluff rice with fork; sprinkle with cheese and continue baking for 5 minutes.
