Garnish with bacon.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburg.
Add water and taco mix.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add beans to mixture, then cheeses.
Mix well.
Cook until cheeses melt.
Keep heated on low in crock-pot.
Serve with corn chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into 2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1/2 hour; uncover and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: saint andrew's night shortbread
directions: Cream the sugar and butter at room temperature with hands until smooth.
Add flour, kneading and blend until dough comes away from sides of bowl.
Press out with fingertips on ungreased, floured cookie sheet.
Prick with fork.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool, but cut in squares while still hot.

title: poppy seed sour cream muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease 12 muffin cups.
In a large bowl combine flour, salt, poppy seed and baking soda.
In a medium bowl with an electric mixer beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Reduce speed and beat in eggs, one at a time. Beat in sour cream and vanilla.
With a rubber spatula fold into flour mixture just until moistened.
Batter will be lumpy. Divide batter among muffin cups. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sarah's cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, instant pudding, water, salad oil, sour cream and eggs together.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Combine brown sugar and ground cinnamon.
Swirl sugar mixture through batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes in pan.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes. Mix in 1 1/2 cups peanuts.
Stir and microwave on High 5 more minutes.
Add baking soda, vanilla and margarine or butter.
Stir quick and dump on buttered baking sheet.
Smooth out quickly. When cool, break into pieces.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream or mix well the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Mix well.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
These are soft cookies.

title: lemon dreams
directions: Mix well butter, 1/4 cup powdered sugar and flour.
Press in an 8-inch square pan (like a pie crust).
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: almond ricotta creme
directions: Mix together the Ricotta, extract and sweetener in a dessert bowl. Serve chilled and sprinkled with toasted almonds.

title: cherry angel cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices; arrange half of the slices on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish. In large mixer bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, water and extract; mix well. Add pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Spread half the cream mixture over cake slices; top evenly with 1 can cherry pie filling. Top with remaining cake slices, cream mixture and cherry pie filling. Chill 4 hours. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: banana bread or muffins
directions: Mix together as listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican lasagna(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cooked meat and onion. Saute in skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce, chilies, taco seasoning and water.
Layer half of the tortillas in a sprayed casserole dish.
Pour half of the meat mixture over the tortillas.
Sprinkle half of the cheese. Repeat layer. Bake for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Grease 10 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients in blender on high speed for 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
If you don't have a blender, use a mixer on medium speed about 2 minutes.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Cut each acorn squash lengthwise in half.
Discard seeds. Place acorn squash halves, cut side up, in a 12-inch skillet.
Add about 1/2 inch of water to skillet.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover skillet and cook 10 minutes or until squash is fork-tender.
Carefully drain liquid from squash cavities.

title: no-cholesterol cake
directions: Cream
margarine
and
sugar well.
Using wooden spoon, stir in	other
ingredients
except
egg whites.
Fold in egg whites. Spoon
into greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.	Bake at	350°
for
1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: low-fat fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook fettucini in large pot according to package directions. Drain water, leaving noodles in pot.
Stir in evaporated milk, cheese and white pepper.
Cover until cheese is melted.
Toss and serve while hot.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion, celery and parsley in butter or oleo.
Add to beef or chicken broth.
Add rice; bake for 1 hour.

title: don's stir-fry cajun strips
directions: Season pork strips with Cajun seasoning.
Toss pepper, apple and pecans with remaining seasonings and reserve.
Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium to high heat.
Stir-fry pork strips without crowding.
Remove and keep warm.
Add the pepper-apple mixture; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Return pork to skillet and stir to mix well.
Serves 4.
Serve with hot rice and tossed green salad.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar and cornstarch.
Stir water in gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil one minute.
Slowly stir at least 1/2 of the hot mixture into egg yolks, then blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil one minute longer, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in butter, lemon juice and lemon rind. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: vegetable-cheese-barley bake
directions: Heat oil in a large, heavy skillet and saute garlic and onions until softened, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables and saute, stirring a few times, for 5 minutes.
Add barley, tomato broth and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: bridal punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl. Pour 7-Up; stir. Yields 50 (4-ounce) servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Whip cream until fairly stiff peaks form.
Fold lime juice and condensed milk into whipped cream.
Smooth mixture into crust. Freeze until firm.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen; place in shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over fish.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours or chill for 4 to 6 hours, turning steaks occasionally.
Drain, reserving marinade.

title: butter sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thickened.

title: zucchini crab cakes
directions: Grind zucchini and let set overnight to drain.
Combine drained zucchini with remaining ingredients; make into patties and fry.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, grapes and orange sections.
Chill while you pare the dressing.
Mix together other ingredients; pour over chicken and fruit.
Mix well.
Cover; let chill for several hours (the longer the better).
Serve on lettuce, sprinkling top with almonds.
Serves 8.

title: asparagus and pasta
directions: Cook fettuccine, just until al dente; drain.
In saucepan, over medium heat, saute garlic, parsley and basil in olive oil.
Add drained fettuccine and asparagus.
Toss carefully so that asparagus is not mashed or crushed.
Pile onto a large serving platter.
In saucepan, heat cream and milk just to boiling point and add the cheese; pour over pasta.
Cover with pepper and a dash of extra Parmesan.

title: easy french-cut bean casserole
directions: Cook beans according to directions on package.
Drain.
Do not overcook.
Place in casserole dish.
Season with salt and pepper as desired.
Toast almonds and mix with beans.
Spread mushroom soup over beans.
Crumble French fried onions over top.
Can be prepared ahead and kept in refrigerator until ready for final preparation.

title: grandmother aull's easiest chicken
directions: Mix the 3 cans of soup and rice together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place the chicken pieces on top of the soup mixture. Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Bake in a 300° oven for 2 hours.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all together 4 to 6 hours prior to serving.
Keeps well for week in refrigerator.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Prepare rice and keep warm.
Heat oil in wok or heavy iron skillet.
Cook chicken with onion, peppers, water chestnuts and carrots quickly while turning frequently.
Add mushrooms and pineapple; heat through.
Serve over rice.
Add soy sauce to preferred taste.

title: dr. maggs' microwave mini meat loaf
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well and shape into a 6 x 4-inch loaf.
Place in an 8 x 4-inch loaf dish. Microwave at power level Medium-high
(170°) for 15 to 20 minutes or until beef is no longer pink, rotating the dish once. Cover loosely with aluminum foil.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Remove from dish and enjoy!
Yields 4 servings.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix together all juices.
Best to mix juices together and chill ahead.
Pour into punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: souper easy quiche
directions: In a medium bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add soup and cream, mixing well.
Sprinkle cheese, meat and vegetables evenly over pie crust.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together.
Bake in two 9-inch round cake pans or 13-inch sheet pan.
Cool before icing!

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Lightly brown mushrooms in olive oil.
Cover with French dressing.
Add garlic.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight. Serve on toothpicks.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all together cold and store in covered container in refrigerator.
These keep for months and are delicious.

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine and cook butter, sugar and milk, stirring constantly to soft ball stage.
Put chocolate chips and marshmallows into large bowl.
Toss together gently and add cooked mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Beat until thick and add walnuts.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
You can also use butterscotch chips instead of chocolate chips.

title: pie filling cake
directions: Can use cherries and chocolate cake mix for Black Forest Delight.
Can also use light ingredients for weight conscious people.

title: chicken divone
directions: Mix together cream of chicken soup, the mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice; set aside.
Cook frozen broccoli.
Boil chicken breasts, then pick off bone (small pieces).
In baking pan, put layer of broccoli, layer of chicken and layer of gravy. Top with cheese and crumbled bread.
Serve with rice.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding (both boxes) with milk until thick.
Add Cool Whip until well blended.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 layer of graham crackers (do not crush).
Put 1/2 of mixture on the graham crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers on top of mixture.
Put remaining pudding mixture on top of graham crackers. Put another layer of graham crackers on top of mixture.
Cover graham crackers with chocolate frosting.
Chill 1 hour.
Enjoy!!

title: cheese patties
directions: Cream oleo and cheese.
Add flour, salt and sauce.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Form in small ball; place on cookie sheet and press with fork into patties.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Add flour and cinnamon; stir in applesauce and nuts.
Mix well and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: mexican lentils and rice
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, warm the oil for 30 seconds.
Add the carrots, peppers and onions; saute for 2 minutes.
Add the rice and lentils; saute for 2 minutes.

title: java fun
directions: Boil chicken breast and remove any bone and skin.
Chunk, slice or dice to suit your taste.
With broth from chicken make gravy. You may have to add some commerical broth for flavor.
Cook rice according to how many people you will be serving.
Put each item in a bowl and arrange around the table.
Usually you start with the rice, chicken and then gravy.
Each item is put on top of the other.
This is particularly good with a large group and takes very little preparation.
You may add to or delete any of the items.

title: stuffing in crock-pot
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion, celery, parsley and mushrooms. Pour over bread cubes in a very large mixing bowl.
Add all seasonings and toss well.
Pour in enough broth to moisten.
Add beaten egg and mix well.
Pack lightly into crock-pot.
Cover; cook on high 4 to 5 hours, then reduce to low 4 to 8 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Fry hamburger meat and sausage until brown.
Drain excess fat.
Add peppers and onion.
Cook until done.
Pour in beans and sugar.
Mix well.
Put in pan.
Put bacon bits on top.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nina's rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients (except eggs) in a saucepan. Bring to a boil. Boil 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Place in a container. Mix in yolk/milk mixture. Then fold in stiff egg white.

title: chicken casserole dish(serves 20 to 30)
directions: Brown the celery, onions and peppers in butter or bacon drippings.
Add this to the carrots (cut up and boiled).
Also add noodles and bean sprouts.
Mix all together, using chicken broth to moisten.
Bake 1 hour at 350° and serve hot.

title: coconut mound balls
directions: Cream butter into milk.
Add coconut and sugar.
Freeze 2 hours.
Roll into 1 inch balls; refreeze 20 minutes.
Using a double boiler, melt wax and chocolate.
Stick a toothpick in coconut
balls
and
turn
them in the chocolate.
Let cool on waxed paper.
Remove picks or leave them in.
Store in refrigerator.

title: frona's scaloppino marsala
directions: Dredge, season and brown cutlets.
Stir in marsala and mushrooms.
Cook until desired taste.

title: mock cream cheese spread
directions: Combine ricotta and cream cheese, garlic, pepper and lemon juice in food processor or blender; process until smooth.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine
eggs
and milk.
Beat until well blended.
Add cracker
crumbs
and
set
aside until all liquid is absorbed. Add remaining	ingredients
except cheese to the cracker mixture. Mix well and spoon into casserole.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese while hot.

title: mrs. barrow's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Set aside. Scald milk.
While it is still hot, add shortening, sugar and salt. Stir until dissolved and cool to lukewarm.
Mix with yeast mixture, egg and enough flour to beat with heavy spoon or dough hook in mixer.
Beat well and add remaining flour to knead.
Knead well and put into greased bowl to rise until doubled in bulk.
Make into rolls and place in greased baking dish, rolling each roll lightly in shortening to keep them from sticking together.
Let rise until double again.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: energy-packed chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Lightly coat a no-stick baking sheet with no-stick spray.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a large soup kettle.
Add onion and saute until soft.
Add flour and cook, stirring, for 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and slowly stir in hot chicken stock.
Add and simmer gently for about 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add parsley, seasoned salt and pepper.
Stir in cream or half and half.
Makes about 8 cups or 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken, bone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Combine mayonnaise and soup.
Arrange broccoli in a 3-quart baking dish.
Cover with chicken, then soup mixture and grated cheese.
Melt margarine in saucepan; add crumbs and toss until well buttered.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cream pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix pineapple, milk and pudding mix.
Then add sour cream. Pour into crust and top with Cool Whip.
Other fruit may be used. If making 1 pie, use:

title: english trifle
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Let cool.
Prepare pudding; set aside.
In a deep glass bowl, crumble a layer of cake.
Place a layer of pudding on top followed by a layer of strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip and repeat layers until bowl is full.

title: aunt martha's cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and shortening together.

Take out 1 cup of mixture to put on top of cake. Combine all other ingredients to remaining flour mixture and mix well. Put batter in prepared pan and sprinkle top of cake with the 1 cup of flour mixture.
Bake at 350° until done when tested.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, three at a time, and mix well.
Add vanilla, flour and soda.
Last add nuts and coconut.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Add peanut butter; beat until cool.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: "red eye" ripe tomato relish
directions: Peel tomatoes without scalding.
Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand overnight.
In the morning, drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix on and off all day. Put in clean pint canning jars.
May be refrigerated.

title: wilma's cupcake filling
directions: Cook flour and milk over low heat until thick.
Stir so it won't burn.
Set aside to cool.
Cream remaining ingredients 5 minutes (no less).
Add flour mixture to this and cream 5 minutes more (no less).

title: jeff's bachelor hors d' oeuvres
directions: Spread cream cheese
on serving plate.	Mix together catsup and horseradish and spread over cream cheese. Top with artificial crab.
Serve
with crackers.

title: jello mold
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add yogurt and Cool Whip.
Mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: small pizzas
directions: Brown ground beef or sausage with onion.
Add oregano, garlic salt and tomato paste.
Spoon mixture onto biscuits and top with sharp and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: y-u-m-m salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Add cream cheese, lime jello, pineapple and mayonnaise; mix well.
Fold in Dream Whip and chill. Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate ice cream sauce
directions: Combine chocolate and cream in top of double boiler.
Cook over boiling water, stirring occasionally, until smooth.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add enough hot mixture to make a smooth paste.
Combine paste with hot mixture in double boiler.
Cook until smooth and slightly thick, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans, butter and vanilla.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 2 cups.

title: fabulous fried onion rings
directions: Batter:
Combine flour and beer in a large bowl and blend thoroughly, using a whisk.
Cover the bowl and allow the batter to sit at room temperature for no less than 3 hours.

title: butterscotch crunch
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in large bowl in microwave just until completely melted.
While still hot, mix in nuts and chow mein noodles.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let stand until cool.
If mix begins to harden before you finish, put back in microwave for a few seconds.
Quick and easy; makes a lot.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine vinegar, olive oil and seasonings.
Pour over mushrooms.
Chill several hours before serving.
You may use the same marinade for 1 pint sliced raw mushrooms, but leave them in the marinade for 24 hours.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pack all of mixture in cracker box.
Refrigerate.
Will keep for months.

title: jambalaya
directions: Season and brown chicken in oil over medium heat.
Add sausage; saute with chicken.
Remove both from the pot.
Add flour to make a roux or roux-like product like Kitchen Bouquet (1 to 2 tablespoons).
Saute onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic in oil until soft.
Return meat to pot.
Add liquid ingredients, salt, pepper and other spices; bring to a boil.
Add rice; return to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Turn rice quickly from top to bottom; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Add green onions.

title: spoon bread ham supper
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter for 5 minutes.
Combine corn muffin mix, ham, 2 tablespoons butter, eggs, milk, mustard and 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Add onion; mix just until blended. Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese, 2 tablespoons butter and sesame seed.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut in wedges and serve hot with Mushroom Sauce.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend together in blender and bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 60 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Put the topping on the mixture and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: chicken stew(serves 6)
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
In a frying pan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook, stirring, until opaque outside, about 10 minutes.
Remove chicken from pan with a slotted spoon.
Add onion, bell pepper, garlic and curry powder to pan.
Cook, stirring, until onion and pepper are tender, about 3 minutes.
Return chicken to pan.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, partly covered, 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or couscous.

title: zucchini stir-fry
directions: Chop or slice zucchini.
Add onion.
Stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Add cheese; toss and serve.
Very quick and delicious.
I use garlic butter to saute veggies.

title: chicken divan
directions: Barely cook broccoli and arrange in 7 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken or turkey on top.
Combine cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken or turkey.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil corn-on-the-cob for 2 minutes, then cut off cob.
Mix all ingredients and cook for 20 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and adjust lids.
Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: honey ham tortilla rolls
directions: Beat ham and cream cheese together until smooth.
Stir in pineapple. Spread 1/4 cup mixture on tortilla; top with spinach. Roll each tortilla, starting at one edge.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 to 8 hours.
To serve, cut each tortilla roll into 1/2-inch slices.
Makes appetizers for 8.

title: beer and cheese soup
directions: Saut the diced vegetables in butter. Mix flour and mustard into sauteed vegetables. Add the chicken or vegetable stock to mixture and cook for 5 minutes. Break broccoli into small flowerets; cut stems into bite-size pieces. Steam until tender-crisp. Add beer and cheeses to the soup. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Check seasonings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Heat fruit to boiling point; sweeten to taste.
Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into mixing bowl.
Add milk, beaten egg and melted butter; mix lightly.
Arrange fruit in bottom of baking dish.
Spread batter over hot fruit.
Bake until brown.

title: whiskey chicken
directions: Butter chicken; sprinkle it with lemon juice and roast about 1 1/2 hours until deep golden brown.
Remove bird; carve and place on warm plate.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook
the
vegetables
a
little.
Thin soup with milk. Layer casserole
dish with broccoli, cauliflower and Brussels sprouts. Cover with soup and sprinkle some Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diet vegetable soup
directions: Eat any time for meals and in between meals.
Nothing there to add weight.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a large saucepan over low heat.
Cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg (beaten until foamy).
Sift together baking soda, flour, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture.
Mix well.

title: trivillian's colombian white chili
directions: Drain cooked beans; add chicken broth.
Saute chopped onions; add chopped cilantro, garlic powder, cumin, cloves and cayenne. Add to beans, bring to a simmer and cook a few minutes.
Add oregano and chilies last (they darken if added earlier).
Stir in chicken pieces.
Heat through.

title: okra gumbo with rice
directions: Cut okra into 1/2-inch rings.
Cook onion in bacon fat until tender.
Drain off fat.
Add chopped bacon, okra, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer until tender (about 30 minutes).
Serve hot with cooked rice.

title: herbed chickennederland, texas
directions: Make a paste of ingredients and spread evenly over cut up chicken, skin side up.
Bake in low side pan, pieces not touching, at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: ardith's pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in margarine.
Add onion, celery, pepper, tomatoes and 1 cup water.
Cover and simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes on low heat.
Mix cornstarch and 1 cup water.
Stir in with rest of ingredients.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Serve on rice. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix together the coconut and sour cream; reserve 1 cup.
This makes the filling.
Add the reserved cup of filling to the Cool Whip and ice cake.
Store 2 days in refrigerator before serving.

title: 3 layer dessert
directions: Mix and press first 3 ingredients in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°; let cool.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with pretzels.
And for a great veggie dip, just use sour cream instead of cream cheese.

title: cherry chocolates
directions: Drain cherries; set aside.
Melt margarine, then stir in marshmallow cream and powdered sugar, one cup at a time; mix well. Make small round balls, flatten them out, place cherry in center and roll and seal.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Put chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Put paraffin in pan and melt it with chocolate chips.
After wax is almost melted, put in the almond bark.
Take a toothpick and dip each cherry in chocolate.
Place on wax paper.
You can use the candy dough for mints and mound coconut bars.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and cook until well blended and hot.

title: crab fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook fettucine; drain.
Stir in butter, cheese, whipping cream, egg yolk and crab meat.
Serve.

title: tasty chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill.
Delicious with Town House crackers.

title: cheese and pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, flour, sugar and cheese together.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and pour 1 stick of melted butter on top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Use 9 x 12 casserole dish or large pie plate.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all other ingredients.
Add margarine. Let dough rise for 2 hours.
Take small amount of dough, twist and tie dough in various shapes.
Let rolls set for another 2 hours. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Yields about 3 dozen rolls.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
Grind the peppers in blender.
Mix with vinegar, sugar and hot pepper.
Bring to rolling boil and add Certo, bringing to full rolling boil again and stirring for one minute.

title: "peachy" fruit salad
directions: Mix lemon juice over sliced bananas.
Add rest of ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: dumplings for a brown stew
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add milk.
Take a teaspoonful at a time and drop into the boiling stew.
Cook 10 minutes without lifting the pot cover.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread and pour half over stiffly beaten egg whites.
(Beat as you pour in with an electric mixer.)
Cook remaining half until it hardens in 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into first mixture and beat until creamy.
When it thickens, drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: lokshen kugel(dairy)
directions: Grease 3-quart ovenproof dish with some of butter.
Cook noodles in large quantity of boiling, salted water for 8 to 10 minutes, until tender; drain well.

title: lo-cal russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients and store in a jar with a tight lid.
Use 1 teaspoon of mix for each cup of boiling water.

title: tuna patties
directions: Roll crackers in paper bag.
Mix ingredients together.
Put oil in frying pan on high heat for a few minutes, then turn down the heat on low.
Put patties in frying pan for 5 to 10 minutes. Don't overcook.
They are real good.

title: chicken divan soup
directions: Heat the roasted garlic butter and oil in soup pot.
Add the chicken pieces and cook until chicken changes color.
It is not necessary to brown the chicken.
Remove from pot and add onions and mushrooms and saute until tender.
Sprinkle the flour over the top of the onion/mushroom mixture and stir.
Add the chicken, broth, broccoli, and half and half.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to medium low.
Cook for about 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir in butter and cheese.
Cook until soup begins to thicken.
Add pepper, thyme, and salt.

title: lemon chicken oregano
directions: Combine butter, seasoning and lemon juice.
Put chicken in baking pan and brush both sides with seasoned butter.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Mix mayonnaise, garlic, onion and seasonings and add to vegetables, then toss with cooked pasta.

title: baked chicken and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Season chicken with Accent and Nature's seasoning to taste (salt if wanted).
Peel and quarter vegetables; cut celery into 2-inch pieces.
Spray pan with Pam.
Arrange vegetables on bottom of pan; season lightly.
Place chicken on top.
Pour margarine or Butter Buds over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes or until done.

title: microwave corn-on-the-cob
directions: Discard soiled outer portion of husk.
Soak corn in cold water 10 minutes.
Drain, but do not dry.
Arrange corn in spoke fashion on microproof plate.
Cook on High 11 to 12 minutes, rearranging halfway through cooking time.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Peel and discard husks and silk.
Serve with butter, salt and pepper.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a large bowl and set aside. Mix together all dry ingredients and gradually add to wet mixture. Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: With a whisk, mix egg, oil, milk, water and vanilla in a bowl. In another bowl, blend pancake mix, sugar and baking powder. Gradually add dry ingredients to liquid mixture, mixing well with a whisk.
Cook pancakes on a slightly greased griddle over medium heat using about 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
When top of pancake is dry, turn and cook 2 minutes longer.
This recipe makes thick pancakes.
For thinner pancakes, increase water to 2/3 cup.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Saute onion in a little water until half cooked.
Mix all ingredients except hash browns and butter.
Put thawed hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and pour mixture over the top of potatoes.
Sprinkle cornflakes over casserole and dribble melted butter evenly over cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until casserole is slightly browned and bubbly.

title: fudgesicles
directions: Add milk to pudding and stir.
Add sugar and evaporated milk. Let set 5 minutes.
Pour into containers and freeze.
Vanilla flavored pudding can be used as a substitute.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and pour into prepared 9-inch pastry.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream together sugar, butter or margarine and egg.
Sift together flour, nutmeg, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Mix together well.
Add raw apples and pecans or other nuts.
Add to sugar mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bill's baked beans
directions: Drain and wash beans.
(I use a flour sifter for this.) Mix beans and other ingredients in a slow cooker and heat for at least 2 hours at low heat.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Lightly fold cocoa into Cool Whip.
In a serving bowl, layer half the pudding, half the brownies, half the Cool Whip and all of the candy.
Repeat layers except for the candy.

title: cabbage and sausage soup
directions: Fry sausage and pour off grease.
Boil onions, potatoes and carrots in with salt and pepper until tender (20 minutes).
Add cabbage and sausage and boil 10 minutes.
Add butter and cream, simmer about 10 minutes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: In a shallow dish, mix together the flour and 1 teaspoon salt; dredge the chicken in the flour mixture.
In a large skillet heat the oil over medium-high heat; saute the chicken for 6 to 8 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.
(At this point, I remove all the fat and do not add margarine.
Continue with rest of recipe.)

title: bran muffins
directions: Bake 3 for 23 minutes.
Makes 60 muffins.
Batter wil keep in refrigerator 6 to 8 weeks.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat together all filling ingredients, adding eggs last, until smooth.
Pour in pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for approximately 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: taco salad
directions: Night Before:
Brown hamburger.
Drain fat. Add taco mix and stir.
Add mayonnaise and blend well.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: tangy-sweet meatballs
directions: Brown meatballs on cookie sheet (with sides) at 350°, shaking gently to cook all sides (20 to 30 minutes) and drain.
Combine rest of ingredients in large saucepan.
Place meatballs in sauce and simmer 1 hour.
Serve warm with toothpicks as an appetizer. Bite-size hot dog pieces may also be placed into the simmering sauce.

title: cinnamon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat until smooth.
Serve with fruit slices or cookies.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 1 cup dip.

title: taco pie
directions: Spray 3-quart casserole with Pam.
Press biscuits into pan forming crust.
Brown meat; add onions, green peppers, tomato sauce, water and mushrooms and taco mix.
Cook until thick.
Pour over unbaked biscuits; top with cheeses.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sparkling punch with lemon ring
directions: Mix chilled ingredients together. Pour over ice ring in large bowl.

title: swedish rice pudding for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a 13 x 24-inch pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: escalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon bacon grease. Add cream cheese and milk to skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Place potatoes, ham and bacon in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour the milk mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Before serving, sprinkle on grated cheese.

title: corn puddin'
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered baking dish.
Place dish in pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm and slightly brown.

title: warm crab appetizer
directions: Add all ingredients together in a crock-pot.
Mix often to avoid sticking to the sides.
Serve with your favorite crackers. Delicious!

title: gingerbread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour square (9 x 9 x 2-inch) pan.
Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 50 minutes.

title: fruit gelatin
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and allow mixture to thicken.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add drained pineapple, sliced bananas and marshmallows.
Congeal until firm in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes covered in boiling salted water until tender. Drain, cool, peel and cut potatoes into cubes.
Place in large bowl.
Sprinkle onion and celery on top.
Mix salad oil, vinegar, and seasonings.
Pour over warm potato mixture.
Toss lightly. Add eggs.
Thin mayonnaise with milk and pour over.
Toss gently and chill.
Serves 12.

title: mocha mix
directions: Makes about 3 cups.
Mix 3 tablespoons of mocha mix with 6 ounces hot water.
Stir and enjoy.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and Karo.
Remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter and Rice Krispies to mixture and spread in a greased pan. Frost with chocolate chips or any other chips desired.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Cool and peel.
Grate on coarse part of grater or use salad shooter.
(Note: Or use frozen shredded hash browns.)
In saucepan, combine butter, sour cream, 1 cup of cheese, green onions and soup (undiluted).
Stir in low heat until blended smooth.
In 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, layer potatoes, soup mixture, potatoes, sour mixture, etc. until all is used. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: lime-cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine all and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf with a slice of stuffed green olive.
Cut in squares.
use 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach; drain and save the juice.
Melt butter and make a white sauce.
Add onion and liquid, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Add seasoning and chopped cheese.
Pour cooked spinach into the sauce.
Put into a casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cover hen with water and add margarine, onion, salt and pepper. Boil for about 3 hours or until meat comes off the bone easily. Cut chicken into cubes and stain the remainder of broth for later use.
Using broth, add enough water to make liquid totaling 6 cups. Add potatoes and carrots, boil 10 minutes.
Do not overcook vegetables.
Save broth again.
Make pie crust.
Layer the chicken and vegetables over the bottom crust, adding green peas last. Using 4 cups of broth and 1 cup flour, stir with whisk until there are no lumps and cook until thickens.
Pour over vegetables in pie.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in eggs and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Into a 2-quart casserole, put 1/2 of noodles, then 1/2 of the meat.
Add one half can cheese soup over the meat.
Repeat this layering.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine eggs and milk in mixing bowl.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to egg and milk mixture.
Heat all in a heavy skillet.
Cover bottom of a funnel with finger.
Remove finger from funnel and release in a circle (round and round) over hot oil.
Turn when golden brown.
Fry on other side.
Drain on paper toweling.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: custard pie
directions: Blend the eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually stir into scalded milk.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until done in center.

title: ribbon fudge
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 6 tablespoons oleo and 1/3 cup milk in saucepan; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate bits until melted.
Add 1 cup marshmallow and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; beat until well mixed.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Repeat with remaining ingredients, substituting peanut butter for chocolate bits.
Spread over chocolate layer. Cool at room temperature.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: veal scalloppine al marsala
directions: Coat scallops, pounded thin, with a mixture of 2 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter in a large skillet. Add garlic and cook until softened.
Add veal and brown on both sides.
Remove veal and place in shallow baking pan.
Add 1 tablespoon butter to pan and brown mushrooms.
Add wine and bring to boil.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Pour over veal.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Add all ingredients together and mix them.
Keep refrigerated.

title: honey lime dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender except oil.
Slowly add Wesson oil.
Makes good dressing for fruit salad.

title: easy holiday cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, Crisco, egg yolks and extract. Gradually blend in dry cake mix.
Dough will be stiff.
(If dough is too soft, chill slightly.
If dough is too dry, add 1 1/2 teaspoons of water and blend well.) Form cookies in one of the following ways.

title: tuna and pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta and rinse immediately with cold water. Let drain completely.
Drain tuna and squeeze out excess liquid. Mix tuna, pasta and Miracle Whip together until well coated.
Add celery seed and dill and mix well.
Add pepper, onion, celery and pickles (or relish) and mix thoroughly.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.
Serves about 6.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel large potatoes and soak in cold water several hours. Grate potatoes and drain.
Add grated onion and beaten eggs.
Stir in salt and flour.
Drop batter by spoonful onto a hot, well-greased frypan or griddle.
Turn to brown other side.
Serve hot with applesauce or sour cream.

title: creamed tuna divan
directions: Thoroughly drain tuna, break up with a fork into large chunks.
Mix soup with milk and stir until completely smooth. Fold in tuna.
Arrange broccoli in an ovenproof serving dish.
Top with tuna mixture and crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes until sauce is bubbly and bread crumbs are nicely browned.
Serves 2

title: country ham balls
directions: With fingertips, mix cheese, ham, flour, butter and enough water to make a stiff dough.
Roll dough into small balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet; bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Can be made ahead and frozen until ready to bake.

title: cheese cake
directions: Sprinkle crumbs over bottom of spring-form pan.
Beat 3 packages of cream cheese and slowly add sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Pour over crumbs and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy french potato vegetable soup
directions: Wash all vegetables and cut into chunks.
In large pot, saute leeks in butter.
Add rest of vegetables and cover with water. Boil until vegetables are tender.
Add College Inn, salt and pepper and cook about 15 minutes more.
Let cool slightly and add half and half.
Blend mixture in blender a little at a time and pour into another pot.
Garnish with sherry and croutons.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Spray sides and bottom of 9 x 13 pan or dish. Lightly butter bread and arrange in dish. Be sure to have a solid layer of bread. Add pieces as needed. Cover bread with sausage, then grated cheese. Beat eggs in bowl and add
half and half, mustard and salt. Pour over casserole and refrigerate overnight.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Blend next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Add meat and other ingredients to mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kahlua balls
directions: In
food
processor,
crush
Oreo cookies.
Add 1/3 cup Kahlua to	start
and
add
more, if necessary, to cookie mix. Mix well and roll in balls, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: fried bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until the particles are fine.
Add milk all at once.
Stir until dough clings together.
Heat 8-inch skillet with 1 tablespoon shortening. Turn down to simmer and spread dough evenly over skillet.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes, then turn and cook for another 10 minutes.
Watch so as not to burn.
Serve hot with butter and jelly.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together.
Combine next 2 ingredients in a large bowl. Pour first 3 ingredients over the cereal mixture and mix well. Form into small balls, approximately 100.
Melt the chocolate pieces and paraffin in a double boiler. Dip balls in it.
Cool on wax paper.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together pudding, cake mix, eggs, oil, water and sour cream for 3 minutes. Fold in grated German chocolate and chocolate chips. Bake in Bundt pan 50 minutes at 350°.

title: recipe for making a home
directions: Take 1 cup of Friendship and add 1 cup of Thoughtfulness.
Mix well together with Tenderness, lightly beaten into a bowl of Loyalty to which has been added 1 cup of Faith, 1 cup of Hope and 1 cup of Charity.
Be sure to add 1 teaspoon of Gaiety that sings and has ability to laugh at little things.

title: baked apricots
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Divide ingredients in half.
Layer in order and repeat.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-cauliflower slaw
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower and onions.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper to make dressing.
Pour over chopped mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Line it with bread.
Brown sausage and drain off grease.
Place sausage on top of bread; add grated cheese. Beat eggs, 1 1/2 cups milk and the dry mustard. Pour on top.
Sprinkle with chopped green onions (tops included). Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix soup and milk and pour over the top of the casserole.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until set.

title: quick golden stew
directions: In a large saucepan, combine carrots, potatoes, onions and just enough water to cover. Cook, covered, on medium-high heat until vegetables are tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain water. Stir in soup and cheese.
Heat through (medium heat).

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook lasagna in 6 quarts boiling water until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain, rinse with cold water and drain again.
Cook potatoes in salted water, drain and mash.
Add cheese to hot mashed potatoes and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: salsa
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Simmer 35 to 40 minutes.

title: western beef casserole
directions: Set oven to 350°.
In skillet, cook and stir beef until red is gone.
Combine soup mix, water, catsup, mustard and vinegar.
Then add to meat in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir in beans.
Bake in preheated oven just until mixture is heated through and bubbling (around 30 minutes).

title: hidden valley potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in big squares.
Boil until tender.
Mix water, mayonnaise, onion and spices (to suit taste).
Add water to get the right thickness.
Add to potatoes.

title: lazy ranch dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate. Serve with vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 3/4 cups.

title: macaroni, cheese and hamburger casserole
directions: In a frying pan, crumble the ground beef, brown and drain the fat.
Cook the macaroni in boiling water per package directions. In a 2 quart baking dish mix the milk, butter, soup, and powdered cheese sauce.
Mix until smooth.
It is easier to mix if you warm it sightly in the microwave.
Add the ground beef and drained macaroni and stir until mixed.

title: ellen's brussels sprouts
directions: Cook sprouts until about half done in water, bouillon and soy sauce.
Drain off water.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of butter and saute until done.
Serve immediately.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Line bottom of dish with beef slices.
Top with chicken breasts.
Combine soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: christmas salad
directions: Combine water and candies, stirring until melted.
Dissolve jello in this water.
Add applesauce and mix well.
Half congeal to consistency of thick egg whites.
In another bowl, mix cream cheese and milk.
Fold in nuts, celery and apples.
Fold this mixture into half congealed mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: spinach pie
directions: Beat cheeses together; add eggs, onion, oil, salt, pepper and spinach.
Brush bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with butter.
Put 10 sheets of philo dough; place filling on top of dough and place 10 more sheets of dough.
Butter in between each one.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: red and green salad
directions: Mix together oil, vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic. Beat or shake to blend.
Gently stir dressing into cabbage and Brussels sprouts just before serving, along with cheese and green onion.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, drained pineapple, bell pepper, onion, seasoned salt and 1 cup of chopped nuts with hands in bowl. Let sit in refrigerator until chilled.
Then shape into balls.
I usually get four small ones or 2 large ones out of this recipe. Then roll them in pecans or coconut.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, then add oil, beaten eggs and pumpkin.
Beat well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Then frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: frosty mandarin dessert
directions: Drain oranges, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add measured liquid.
Add sherbet by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened. Fold in oranges, reserving a few for garnish.
Pour into serving bowl or individual serving dishes.
Chill until set; at least one hour.
Garnish with reserved mandarin orange sections and mint leaves, if desired.
Makes about 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: "sock it to me cake"
directions: Mix the cake mix, pudding mix, sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and sour cream together.
Mix the brown sugar and cinnamon together (mix well with your hand).
Put half of the batter in a greased and floured pan. Spread the brown sugar over the batter.
Put the rest of the batter over this.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: thirty minute rolls
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt, margarine and heat until lukewarm. Combine yeast and flour and add to water.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Put into greased oven proof container.
Cover with a lid or foil.
Turn oven on at 425° for ONE MINUTE and TURN OFF!!
Put container in oven for 15 minutes. Remove and shape as desired.
Can be baked immediately or let set for 30 minutes.
Bake at

title: honey mustard pork chops
directions: You will need 1 large Reynolds oven bag.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Wipe meat with damp cloth.
Place oil in heavy saucepan and heat.
Place meat in
pan
and
brown
on
all sides.
Add water, onion and potatoes.
Cover
and
simmer slowly over low heat until tender, about 3 or 4 hours.
Serve hot.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with pretzels, nuts and sugar.
Press into 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes; cool.
Beat together cream cheese, 1 (8 ounce) carton Cool Whip and sugar. Spread on top of pretzel mix.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
When thickened, pour over cheese mixture.
Spread 1 (8 ounce) carton Cool Whip over strawberries.
Decorate with chopped pecans.

title: half pound cake
directions: Cream
butter,	gradually
add	sugar
until smooth and creamy.
Add
yolks and flour alternately, blending well after each addition.
Beat
whites
until
stiff, but not dry.
Fold whites into
sugar	and butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for
hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. This may be doubled to make a full pound.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pack firmly into a loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand for five minutes and serve. Yield 8 servings.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in blender.
Pour into lightly greased pan (glass plate).
Let settle for 2 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pear-apple preserves (pearable)
directions: Pare fruit and mix with sugar and lemon.
Cook slowly until syrupy and thick.
(Fruit should be clear and tender.)
Cool and pack in jars and seal.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar.
Add eggs, beating in one at a time.
Pour into well-greased oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
While still warm, pour icing over it.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In large shallow roaster or cake pan, combine popcorn and nuts.
Place in 250° oven while preparing glaze.

title: teriyaki beef bok choy
directions: Marinate beef pieces approximately 1 hour in teriyaki sauce, making sure all pieces are covered.
Heat wok (high) and add oil, coating sides.
Take pieces of beef out of liquid and put into wok, stirring until all sides are braised medium.
Add all vegetables, turning in pan until covered with drippings.
In small bowl, mix cornstarch in water until silky.
Pour remaining teriyaki liquid in middle of wok with beef and veggies pushed toward the side.
When liquid bubbles, add cornstarch slowly until thickened, not thick. In saucepan, boil water; add equal amount of rice.
Cook per instructions.
Pour beef and vegetables over rice.
Feed 3 to 5 people.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Chill and then form into balls and flatten with a fork.
After baking, roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: buttermilk pie 1
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Add flour and eggs, one at a time. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake, this tends to make the pie watery.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls in hot shortening.
Roll in powdered sugar when done.

title: grammy's cornbread muffins
directions: Beat all ingredients well. Preheat oven to 475°. In muffin tin, add 1/4 teaspoon cooking oil and put in oven until hot. Take pan out of oven and put mix in the tin. Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 1 1/2-quart dish. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk. Beat well. Pour over top of melted margarine. Do not stir. Pour heated fruit over flour mixture. Bake until pastry rises to top and is brown (375° for approximately 30 minutes).

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix melted margarine and peanut butter together.
Add powdered sugar, little by little.
Roll into small balls and chill overnight.
Melt chocolate disks and dip balls, then place on wax paper and chill to set.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a 3 1/2 x 6-inch loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool on a cake rack.
Pour chocolate sauce over cake and serve.

title: congealed salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package.
As it starts to gel, add the other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator to set.

title: chicken bake
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water with onion, celery and seasonings of your choice.
Cool, remove skin and cut into chunks. Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and cream.
Mix until smooth.
Add broccoli, cheese and mushrooms.
Mix, spoon over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet & sour red cabbage
directions: Fry bacon with onion until bacon is crisp and the onion is tender. Stir in brown sugar and vinegar. Stir in cabbage. Add water and salt; cook over medium heat until cabbage is tender about 20-30 minutes, if desired cook the tasty cabbage with 1 diced apple.

title: fudge sauce for ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add part of milk and stir into a smooth paste.
Add rest of the milk.
Cook until thick, stirring often.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Cook 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab salad
directions: Shred crab, add all ingredients together and put in enough Mayo to make moist.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello and tapioca pudding mixes with the boiling water. Let jell.
Add the Cool Whip and pineapple.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir hamburger and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper and spread in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: no fuss pork chops
directions: In large skillet, heat oil. Add pork chops and brown on both sides. Add onions and cook until tender.

title: green rice(hand me down)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Mix everything in an oven-safe bowl and cook for about 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: mom's "goulash"
directions: Brown
ground
beef
in
large skillet; drain.	Quarter potatoes, carrots and onions and place on top of browned beef. Add water to fill pan to depth of 1/2-inch and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring
to
simmer.	Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Serves 4.

title: peanutty crunch snack mix(quaker)
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Place cereal and peanuts in large bowl. Set aside.
In 1-cup glass measuring cup or small microwavable bowl, combine peanut butter and honey.
Microwave at High 30 seconds.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour over cereal.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
As soon as you remove from oven, pour 1 large can of crushed pineapple on top.
Make instant vanilla pudding according to directions and pour over cooled cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top. Cool for several hours before serving.

title: icing for pies
directions: Add Marshmallow Creme to beaten egg whites.
Beat about 5 or 10 minutes longer and spread on pie; bake until lightly brown.
Makes enough for two small pies.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and pour in hot greased iron skillet.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dietetic apple pie
directions: Tart apples are blended with sour cream to make a delicate, custardy filling for this pie.
A crunchy topping adds contrast in texture and flavor.

title: red raspberry salad
directions: Add Jell-O to boiling water.
When dissolved, add frozen raspberries and applesauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in large dish or mold.
Top with fruit dressing when firm.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar. Add 1 cup flour at first.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add milk, then remaining 2 cups flour.
Mix undrained pineapple.
Preheat oven to 325°. Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: fritter batters(for deep-fried foods)
directions: Beat well until smooth.
Stir about 1 cup of chosen food into batter.
Drop by tablespoons into hot fat and fry about 5 minutes or until golden brown and thoroughly cooked.

title: joggin' in a jug
directions: Drink 2 ounces a day to help keep your cholesterol in check.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar and Crisco until well blended; beat well.
Add eggs and syrup and beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Bake 5 to 9 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Put yeast in warm water; set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients. Add egg and yeast water.
Mix well.
Make rolls and put in cake tins lightly floured.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Will keep 3 to 4 days in fridge.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together, pour in casserole dish and sprinkle with crackers or bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Chopped onions and pimentos can be used.

title: peanut clusters made easy
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Stir in milk and peanuts. Drop by teaspoon on buttered cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: christmas cranberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve in punch bowl.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut chicken in pieces and put in bottom of large casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup, chicken broth and margarine together. Pour over chicken.
Beat Bisquick and milk and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green pea and cheese salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Toss with salad dressing and mustard.
Add more salad dressing, if desired.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 10.

title: cranberry coffee cakes
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together well.
Beat remaining ingredients except cranberries well and add to first mixture.
Put batter in loaf pans.
Fill half full, spread some cranberries over batter and top with more batter.
Bake in 375° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: lemon barbecued meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, mix well first 6 ingredients.
Shape mixture into 6 individual loaves; place in a baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: company pork chops
directions: Place chops in a well buttered baking dish.
Add apple cider until it's level with chops.
Place thinly sliced apples on chops. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: buttered rum rolls
directions: In small saucepan, combine the first 1/4 cup brown sugar and flour.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture thickens and bubbles. Remove from heat and stir in rum extract.
Divide brown sugar mixture evenly among 8 ungreased muffin cups; set aside.

title: doughnuts(kid recipe)
directions: Heat about 2 inches oil in skillet on medium high heat.
Place biscuits on floured, waxed paper.
Using small cap (such as syrup top), cut a hole in the center of each biscuit.
Gently put biscuits in hot oil.
Cook until lightly browned.
Flip biscuit. Dip hot biscuit into bowl of powdered sugar.
Presto - powdered doughnut!
Use biscuit centers as doughnut holes.

title: golda's potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into pieces, about 12 to 16 per potato; slice garlic finely widthwise.

Place both, with onion (whole), salt, pepper and enough water to completely cover potatoes in a soup pot. Bring to a boil on high heat, reduce to a simmer and cook, covered, about 10 minutes or less, until potatoes are beginning to be tender, but still resist a fork slightly.
Add pasta, stir, cover and continue cooking until pasta and potatoes are both tender, but not mushy, about 5 minutes.
Remove and discard onion.
Add sour cream all at once and stir thoroughly as it heats; be careful not to break up the potatoes.
Taste and correct seasonings and serve when hot through, but not boiling.
Serves 4. Total preparation time:
40 minutes.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding and eggs well and add 7-Up.
Bake in three 8-inch layer pans or 9 x 13-inch for 30 to 40 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: bev's salad
directions: In a large salad bowl layer ingredients in the order above. Serve immediately.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Prepare chicken by simmering, then take off bones and cut in large pieces and refrigerate.
One hour before serving, take broth from chicken and bring to boil.
Add noodles.
Cook 8 minutes. Set aside.

title: designer pizza
directions: Dip cleaned clams in milk.
Dust with flour, dip in beaten eggs; roll in Ritz cracker crumbs mixed with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Place on tin foil covered cookie sheet sprayed with Pam. Arrange clams and drizzle with melted butter.
Place in oven preheated to 500° for 7 minutes.

title: cheese squares
directions: Combine ingredients; spread on cocktail rye bread. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until cheese melts. Serve hot.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mash hamburger and cook with onion, salt and pepper.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Mound with mashed potatoes on top.
This is a good way to use up leftover mashed potatoes.

title: quick mix
directions: Mix flour and dry milk together in a large bowl.
Cut shortening into flour mixture with two knives or a pastry blender or food processor until mixture resembles small peas.
Store the quick mix at room temperature in clean dry jars or plastic containers with well fitting lids.
Keep tightly covered.

title: golden ginger apples
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add all other ingredients.
Add apples, cored and sliced.
Coat apple slices with the butter mixture; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook longer, if necessary, until apples are tender.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugars, oil and eggs.
Beat until blended.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients; blend well.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Butter and toast lightly 12 English muffin halves.
Brown ground beef and add pizza sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Spread muffins with Cheez Whiz.
Put meat mixture on top.
Refrigerate or freeze.
When ready to use, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and broil.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil over medium heat; remove chicken.
Add onion and celery; fry slowly 15 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms, tomatoes, tomato paste, sherry, sugar and seasonings.
Add water and chicken; cook over low heat until chicken is tender.
Cook spaghetti; then remove chicken from sauce and place in serving dish.
Pour remaining sauce over drained spaghetti.

title: reese's peanut butter balls
directions: Combine and mix well sugar, peanut butter and margarine; chill in refrigerator for several hours.
After chilled, roll mixture into small balls.

title: pickle beets
directions: Cover fresh beets in boiler in water.
Cook until tender.
Pour off hot water; run cold water over beets.
When cool enough, peel beets and slice large beets; if small, leave whole.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together well and roll into meatballs about the size of a quarter.
Place on a well sprayed square pan.
Using one jar Prego or any sauce of choice, pour over meatballs and cover with foil. Cook for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over favorite pasta noodles.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese until well blended. Add enough cherry juice to "color" mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with fresh fruits.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake as directed yellow cake mix, Dream Whip and coconut extract.
While cake bakes mix cream of coconut and sweetened condensed milk.
When cake is done make holes with wooden spoon in cake and pour mixture
over cake.
Cool completely and cover with Cool Whip and top with coconut.

title: new orleans style bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Drain and add 2 quarts of water.
Cook covered 2 1/2 hours.
Add meat, garlic, tomatoes, carrots, celery, etc.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer at least 30 minutes or more; adding water as needed.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in crackers and nuts.
Bake in greased baking dish, 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Spread Dream Whip over top, then add 1 can cherry pie filling.
Chill overnight.

title: oven roasted potatoes - greek style
directions: Mix to equally distribute the spices and bake uncovered in deep pan in 400° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender. After 40 minutes, remove pan from oven and shake the potatoes. Return to oven and leave them undisturbed for the remainder of the time.

title: baked egg casserole
directions: Beat the eggs until well mixed.
Add the browned sausage, milk, cheese and soup.
Mix.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 2 cups croutons. Add the above mixture. Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: banana berry pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Add cold water. Chill until slightly thickened. Mix 1 cup whipped cream and 3/4 cup strawberries. Add to Jell-O mix and pour into pie shell. Chill 15 minutes. Mix pudding and milk. Fold in rest of strawberries. Spread over Jell-O mixes. Chill 2 hours.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake (preferable sheet cake pan).	Let cool completely. Crumble half the cake into glass dish (9 x 13).
Mix melted butter, sugar and cream cheese together.
Fold into the Cool Whip. Layer this mixture over the crumbled cake.	Crush 3 Butterfinger bars and sprinkle over layer.
Repeat for a second layer.
Place into refrigerator until completely chilled several hours or overnight.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss with mayonnaise (or sour cream), salt and pepper.
Chill and serve with crackers.
Makes 20 servings.

title: sour cream cake 1
directions: Combine the sour cream, sugar and butter. Add egg yolks and beat well. Add flour, soda, salt and flavoring. Beat long enough to get flour mixed in good.
Fold in stiff egg whites.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a medium bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in milk, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Stir in rice and raisins.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir rice up from bottom and continue baking for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
Fill pie shell with sliced peaches. Sprinkle with tapioca.
Pour honey over peaches.
Cover peaches with strips of pastry.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: chili cheese bread
directions: Preheat
oven
Toss Bisquick mix with cheese. Stir together remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients. Mix until blended.
Pour
into
greased
9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake
55 minutes.
Cool
10 minutes; remove from pan.
Yield: Makes 1 loaf.

title: bourbon baked beans
directions: About 3 hours before serving time, empty beans into a 2-quart casserole.
Stir in bourbon and coffee.
Cover and let stand at room temperature.
About 1 1/4 hours before serving time, remove cover.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Remove casserole from oven and arrange pineapple around edge of beans.
Return to oven and bake about 15 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: *To make sour milk, add 1 tablespoon vinegar or lemon juice to 1 cup milk.

title: low-fat curried rice salad
directions: Cook rice.
Finely chop green onions and sweet red pepper. Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Combine Italian dressing with vinegar and curry powder.
Add to rice mixture and toss well.
Cover and chill.
About 95 calories per 1/2-cup serving.

title: walnut carrot cake
directions: Chop 1/2 cup walnuts fine.
Grease three 9-inch layer cake pans well.
Sprinkle each with about 2 1/2 tablespoons walnuts to coat. Chop remaining walnuts a little more coarsely; set aside.
Resift flour with baking powder and salt.
Combine sugar, eggs, oil and spices.
Beat at high speed until light and well mixed.
Add half of flour mixture; stir until well blended.
Add milk, then remaining flour.
Stir in carrots and chopped walnuts.
Divide batter evenly in pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until cakes test done.
Let stand in pans on wire racks 10 minutes.
Turn cakes out onto racks to cool.
When cold, frost with a buttercream frosting.
Decorate with walnut halves.
Makes 1 large cake.
Makes 12 servings.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add the flour, baking soda, salt, Ricotta cheese and vanilla.
Dough will be sticky.
Spoon 1/2 tablespoon onto a greased cookie sheet far apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen (iced).

title: frosty punch
directions: Put in blender until mixed.
Makes about 6 (8 ounce) glasses.

title: baked beans
directions: In skillet, brown diced onions and about 5 slices chopped bacon at medium heat.
Then add remaining ingredients except bacon.
Stir well.
Cook on medium heat 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, or put in baking dish top for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: ritzy chicken
directions: In a flat dish, melt butter.
Crumble the Ritz crackers.
Coat the chicken in sour cream and cover with the cracker crumbs.
Dip in the melted butter.
Place on baking sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer, except pecans, add those last. Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours or until well done.

title: sunday roast
directions: Brown roast well on both sides.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add one cup water, Worcestershire sauce and onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 2 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes and bake until veggies are done (30 to 45 minutes) at 300°.
Make gravy from juice.

title: muscatolli and brazollis(country:  italian)
directions: Saute olive oil, garlic and onions in a large pot until soft. Add tomatoes, sauce, paste, water and mushrooms.
Add oregano, basil, parsley, salt, pepper and allspice to taste.
Simmer approximately 45 minutes, uncovered.
While simmering, make brazollis (steak rolls).
Lay steak strips on board or counter top.
Coat steaks with Parmesan, Romano, parsley, Italian seasonings and Mozzarella cheese.
Roll steak and tie with string. (These can be purchased in Italian meat markets already made.) Add steak rolls to sauce and simmer approximately 45 minutes, uncovered.
Tastes best if made the day before.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: rice pudding
directions: Wash rice; place in double boiler and cover with water. Cook until
dry.
Add
milk,
sugar,
salt
and raisins.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla just before removing from stove.

title: american chili
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in oleo until beef loses its pink color.
Add tomatoes, beans, celery, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add chili powder and simmer 30 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box in a medium size bowl.
After pudding is mixed thoroughly, place whole container of Cool Whip in bowl with pudding and mix until completely blended.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in pan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper, chicken bouillon and water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Place potatoes in bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking dish or roaster.
Top with onion rings.
Pour chicken broth mixture evenly over potatoes and onions.
Top with pork chops.
Cover.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Form into small balls and fry until done. Drain on paper towels. Blend catsup and jelly in large saucepan; cook over low heat until jelly is melted. Add barbecue sauce to taste. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add meatballs and heat thoroughly. Place in a chafing dish to serve if desired.

title: chocolate popcorn squares
directions: Mix popcorn, peanuts and coconut.
In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves, then cook at 270°, soft crack stage.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Pour mixture over popcorn, stirring well.
Press into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Immediately cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Melt chocolate and shortening together.
Drizzle over top of squares.

title: corrinne's cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; set aside.
In saucepan, melt butter, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Bring to boil.
Add flour and sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: sausage cheese bake
directions: Combine bread cubes, sharp cheese and sausage in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Pour eggs beaten with 2 1/2 cups milk over.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until melted and thick.
Cool to room temperature.
Line a 9-inch pie tin with vanilla wafers. Alternate layers of ice cream and fudge.
Freeze 3 to 5 hours. Top with pecan halves, if desired.

title: mom's 1-minute french dressing
directions: Combine in covered jar.
Serve on greens, meat, tossed vegetables or fruit salad.
Makes 1 cup.
Shake well before using.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix salt, sugar, shortening and yeast.	Then
add
part of flour; then add eggs and rest of
flour.
Let
rise;
make into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake 15 to 20
minutes in a 400° oven.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter together until crumbly.
Set aside.
Mix molasses, water and soda together and then pour into crumb mixture and mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then reduce oven heat to 375° and bake 30 minutes.

title: ground beef grand style
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Put biscuits on top; bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or until biscuits are done.

title: green salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer all ingredients.
When all are layered, cover completely with mayonnaise and seal edges.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Toss and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down firmly.
Beat next 3 ingredients together for 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread mixture evenly over unbaked graham cracker crust.
Cover with thinly sliced bananas.
On top of this, spread the well-drained pineapple and then top with the whipped topping. Sprinkle cherries and nuts on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
This keeps several days in the refrigerator so it may be made two days ahead of the time you need it.

title: frozen strawberry daiquiri
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a blender.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together; add bananas, then egg. Alternate dry ingredients with milk.
Add walnuts last.
Let stand about 5 minutes before baking (use loaf pan) at 350° for 60 minutes (or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean).

title: deer roast stew
directions: Fix cooking bag by directions.
You have to get in bag twice after it is cooking.
Be careful; very hot.
Put deer in bag.
Add soup mix and cup of water.
Cook this at 300° in oven for 30 minutes.
Cut carrots and celery into chunks.
Along with diced onions, add carrots and celery to deer when 30 minutes is up.
Put back in oven for 30 more minutes.
Peel and cut potatoes into chunks.
Add after the next 30 minutes is up, along with seasoning.
Cook an additional hour.
Open and serve.

title: texas macaroni salad
directions: Chop all vegetables into bite-size pieces.
Drain black olives. Mix all vegetables, olives and cooked, cooled pasta into large bowl.
Pour envelope of dressing over mixture.
Then pour bottle of dressing over that.
Add enough mayonnaise to make moist.
Cover. Serve chilled.

title: mrs. howe's sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and resift 3 times with soda and salt. Melt chocolate over hot water and cool.
Cream shortening, adding sugar gradually; add whole eggs and beat until fluffy and light colored.
