Stir in melted chocolate.
Add flour mixture in small portions alternately with sour cream, stirring well after each addition.
Add vanilla, then stir in boiling water or coffee. Turn into 2 (8-inch) greased cake pans which have been buttered and lined with buttered wax paper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and spread with icing.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and crushed bananas alternately.
Add soda last.
Cook in 2 greased and sugared loaf pans for 45 minutes to 1 hour until done at 375°.

title: squash gems
directions: Beat well the egg.
Add squash, milk, oil and sugar.
Beat well to mix.
Add flour, sifted with salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Blend well.
Turn into greased muffin pans.
Bake in 400° oven about 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: jello "dream" cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to box directions.
Pour cake mix in 2 cake layer pans.
Bake at suggested temperature for suggested time.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Beat eggs in a small mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Set aside.
Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper; spread on plate.
Dip tomato slices in egg.
Coat with cornmeal mixture.
Heat oil and butter in large frypan.
Fry tomato slices until golden brown on both sides.
Remove from pan. Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple chicken crepes
directions: Mix everything together and put aside.

title: salmon patties with yogurt sauce
directions: Combine 1/2 cup yogurt, carrot, celery, 1 tablespoon green onion and 1/4 teaspoon dill.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.

title: easy sour cream flounder
directions: Lightly spray pan with oil.
Place flounder in pan; cover with mixed ingredients.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch (or flour) and sugar with 3 tablespoons cold water.
Stir into hot water in a double boiler.
Cook until thickened (20 to 30 minutes).
Add butter, lemon juice and lemon rind.
(Cook 2 to 10 minutes longer.)

title: grandpa marbut's vegetable soup
directions: You may add other canned vegetables as desired.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Shake pieces in bag filled with cinnamon and sugar.
Put in ungreased Bundt pan.
Pour remaining sugar and oleo over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pasta with chicken and broccoli
directions: Boil spaghetti until al dente; drain.
Heat oil in skillet, add garlic and stir 1 minute.
Add broccoli; saute for 2 minutes or until tender-crisp, then transfer to a heated dish.
Add chicken to skillet and saute until no longer pink, about 5 minutes.
Toss pasta with broccoli and chicken.
Garnish with parsley, sprinkle with pepper and serve.
Serves 6.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Measure popcorn into buttered bowl (4-quart or larger). Combine together in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan the sugar, water, corn syrup, salt and vinegar.
Stir over heat until sugar is dissolved; cover.
Bring to boil and let boil briskly for 3 minutes.
Uncover; insert candy thermometer and cook mixture until hard ball stage, 260°.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir with large buttered spoon.
Immediately form balls; handle gently to avoid packing.
Use butter on hands if necessary.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift meal and flour together.
Add all dry ingredients and onion.
Beat in eggs and catsup.
Mix all other ingredients in and add equal amounts of evaporated milk and water until stiff batter is formed.
Drop into hot oil by teaspoon.
Cook until golden brown.

title: cheesy chili topper
directions: Place unwrapped block of cream cheese on microwavable plate; top with chili and cheese.
Microwave on High for 45 seconds. Sprinkle with cilantro.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: low-fat pineapple cheese cake
directions: Mix together; if too thick, add a little pineapple juice. Pour into crust.

title: rose's peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour in the center of the butter.
Pour peaches into the mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: fried rice
directions: You will also need a 10-inch skillet.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Into a well buttered baking dish, put bread and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and dry mustard slightly and pour over bread and cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 3/4 hour or until firm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, butter, sugar and cream cheese.
These should be soft (room temperature).
Then alternate eggs, flour and flavor. Put in cold oven; set at 300° for 1 hour.

title: coffee vienna
directions: Mix together thoroughly and store in an airtight container. Mix desired amount with water when ready to use.

title: baked stuffed squash
directions: Cut the top from the squash or cut squash in halves lengthwise.
Steam until nearly cooked (1/2 hour or more).
Remove from the water; scoop out inside about 1-inch all around and all the squash from the top.
Sprinkle the inside with salt and add stuffing.

title: caramel pecan rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
In saucepan, heat milk, water, 2 tablespoons white sugar, salt and Crisco until warm.
Stir to melt Crisco.
Add to dry ingredients in mixer bowl.
Beat at low speed 1/2 minute.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn on floured surface.
Knead until smooth.
Cover 20 minutes.
Punch down.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, melted butter and corn syrup.
Cook until blended; spread on bottom of well-greased muffin tin.
Also add nuts.
Roll dough to 2 x 10 x 6-inch.
Spread with softened oleo.
Combine 1/2 cup white sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over dough.
Roll up.
Slice into 1-inch rolls.
Cover; refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
Remove and raise 20 minutes.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Chill it and serve it with crackers or fresh vegetables.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: oven baked german apple pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425.
Combine flour, milk, eggs, and nutmeg. Beat lightly and leave batter a little lumpy.
Divide butter and melt in two 9-inch pie pans.
When pans are hot divide batter equally between pie pans.
Top with sliced apples and bake 15-18 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with your favorite syrup.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Pull each biscuit apart and roll out in flour.
Wrap biscuit around a piece of apple and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use all the biscuits and apples, this will make 20.
In a pan, melt margarine, sugar and water.
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle with apple pie spice or cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
You can serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: fried catfish(modern)
directions: Chop parsley; combine dry ingredients.
Dip fish in mixture and deep fry at 375° until golden brown.

title: corn bread with hamburger
directions: Combine cornmeal, corn, sour cream and eggs.
Heat frying pan and oil.
Pour 1/2 cornmeal mixture into frying pan.
Top with cheese and crumbled ground beef.
Add jalapeno (if you like it hot).
Add onion.
Cover with remaining cornmeal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
(Save 2 ounces of grated Cheddar cheese for topping.)
Bake, covered, in a greased pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Bake another 1/4 hour, uncovered.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Put into a 3-quart saucepan 2/3 cup Pet milk (1 small can), 2 cups miniature (or cut up) marshmallows and the undiluted frozen orange juice.
Stir over medium heat until marshmallows melt; take off heat.
Stir in the 3/4 cup nut meats, 1 cup mixed candied fruit and 1/4 cup candied cherries.
Stir in well a mixture of 4 cups finely crushed graham cracker crumbs, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 teaspoon cloves.
Press firmly into a loaf pan (or pans) lined with wax paper.
Cover tightly.
Chill 2 days.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spray muffin tin with Pam and pour mixture in, filling about 2/3 full.
Bake 12-15 minutes on 450 degrees.

title: stove top noodle, vegetable and ground beef dinner
directions: Bring to a boil 3 cans beef broth or 2 beef bouillon cubes and water.
Add noodles.
Cook until done; add green beans, drained. Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain off grease and add to cooked noodles and beans.
Heat again and serve.
This is also good with a can of mushroom soup added.

title: holiday salad
directions: Combine all ingredients until well coated and blended.
Chill and serve cold.

title: mexican taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook hamburger meat and minced onion together, then drain.
Add taco sauce, salt and pepper and cook together for about 3 minutes.
Add rice and beans to hamburger mixture and stir together.
Take 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, pour tortilla chips on bottom then mash chips and sprinkle with water until they're moist.
Pour mixture on top of chips and layer top with American cheese.
Bake about 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, egg, water and vanilla.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries.
Stir in sugar, apples and pineapple.
Let stand 1/2 hour. Dissolve jello in boiling water and when it starts to congeal, stir in fruit mixture.
Add 1/2 cup nut meats, if desired.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in bowl.
Add eggs, pineapple, water and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Cook in 400° oven until pie begins to brown, then reduce heat to 300° until pie is firm.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mint tea-morocco
directions: Add sugar to boiling water.
Pour over mint leaves in tea pot. Stir.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Pour over 1 fresh mint leaf in each cup.
Serving Size:
Preparation Time:

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Pour broken pecans into pie crust.
Melt chocolate, butter and sugar in double boiler.
Beat eggs; add salt and vanilla.
Stir into chocolate mixture which has cooled partially.
Pour this over the broken pecans in the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Carefully remove stems from caps.
Chop stems.
Trim root end of scallions and then chop scallions, including green tops.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in frying pan. Saute chopped stems and scallions.
Mix with grated cheese in bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Melt remaining butter.
Brush inside and outside of each mushroom cap with butter.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Mound cheese mixture into each cap.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° until mushrooms are cooked and cheese is bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: lemonade syrup
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
When cool, add lemon juice. Pour in fruit jar and seal or put in refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely.
Dilute with cold water to suit taste.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast cake in 1 cup warm water.
Add to egg mixture.
Melt shortening in 1 cup warm water. Add to the same mixture.
Add flour.
Beat in large bowl.

title: hamburger dip(yields 2 quarts)
directions: Saute ground beef until browned.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Spoon into chafing dish and keep warm.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Freezes well.
(Men love this!)

title: fruit waldorf
directions: Mix ingredients and chill before serving.
Serve on lettuce.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Put crackers on sheet cake pan.
Pour butter mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbles.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns, then mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and stir until potatoes are well coated.
Pour into 3-quart casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: pumpkin parfait cake
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine cake mix, pumpkin, eggs, milk, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed until well combined.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping sides of bowl frequently.
Spread batter evenly in a greased 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cool completely on wire rack.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: sunshine delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add oranges, fruit cocktail, pecans and bananas.
Stir gently.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into lightly oiled 9-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.
Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over Jell-O layer and chill slightly.
Pour remaining Jell-O mixture on top.
Refrigerate.

title: venison jerky
directions: Cut venison in strips with grain.
Mix all ingredients and marinate meat overnight.
Remove and dry with paper towels. Place on cookie sheet.
Dry in 200° oven for 6 to 8 hours or until dry to touch.
Cool and store in tightly sealed jar.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Place the 1/2 noodles, the chicken and lettuce in large bowl with water chestnuts and green onion.
Mix sugar, vinegar, hoisin sauce, sesame oil and soy sauce.
Pour sauce over chicken and remaining noodle.
Toss before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Prepare bottom crust by mixing together flour, butter and pecans until crumblike.
Press mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly golden.
Cool.

title: mama mutt's okra creole
directions: Brown okra in 1/2 cup oil in saucepan. Drain okra, removing excess oil.
Put okra aside.
Using remaining 1/2 cup oil, mix flour and brown the flour making a roux.
Add onions and bell peppers to the roux and saute for 3 minutes. Add smoked sausage to roux mixture. Add lima beans to roux mixture.
Add 2 cups water and cook over medium heat for 25 minutes. Add fresh shrimp. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add okra and cook 2 minutes longer.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: veal loaf with pistachios(serves 6)
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Heat the olive oil in a saucepan. Add the scallions, onions and garlic. Saute, stirring for 5 minutes.
Place the veal and the onion mixture in a bowl.
Chop the liver very finely.
Add it to the mixture along with the bread crumbs, parsley and pepper. Blend well.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash up beans until smooth.
Mix eggs, sugar, butter and then add beans.
Stir in rest of ingredients and pour into pie shells. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: By hand, mix all ingredients.
Roll out on floured board. Cut with cutter.
Place on greased sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 20 biscuits.

title: graham cracker torte
directions: Make pudding.
In separate bowl stir until well blended the whipping cream, Nestle Quik, vanilla, coffee and sugar. Refrigerate for 1 hour, then whip until very stiff.
Stack four graham crackers with pudding between each (no pudding on top cracker).
Frost with
whipped topping.
Refrigerate for a few hours.
Keeps well.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes. Cut into large chunks. Place in heavy pan. Cover with water, sugar and butter. Cook slowly about 1 hour on low boil. Watch at the end, the water will have cooked away and the syrup will be thick.

title: magnolia's chocolate pie
directions: Double boil until thick with 1/2 stick butter. Put in baked shell- beat whites and bake slowly until meringue is browned.

title: spinach fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking dish.
Stir together spinach, cheese, lemon juice, salt, pepper and oregano.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place uncooked rice in the bottom of a large casserole (3-quart). Add carrots, onions and celery in individual layers. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover this with the meat. Add the tomatoes and water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry-wine jelly
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Boil 1 minute, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and stir in wine and pectin.
Skim off foam with a metal spoon.
Quickly pour jelly into sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover at once with 1/2 in melted paraffin wax.

title: mexican hot salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in very large bowl.
Put into pint jars or quart jars and store in refrigerator.

title: deviled chicken breasts
directions: Place bread crumbs in large plastic bag.
Add chicken and shake to coat chicken with bread crumbs.
Heat oil in large nonstick pan (skillet) over medium heat.
Cook on each side until browned.
Add wine and next 4 ingredients.
Cover.
Reduce heat and cook 15 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken and mushrooms with a slotted spoon.
Add lemon juice and mustard to skillet. Stir well.
Cook 2 minutes.
Spoon sauce over chicken and mushrooms.

title: easy punch
directions: Freeze cans of juice overnight, then set out of freezer hour before mixing.
Seven-Up should be chilled also.
Mix all together in punch bowl and serve.

title: yummy brownies
directions: Beat the 4 eggs until creamy and slowly add sugar.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Tear cakes into bite size pieces and mix with 1 tub of Cool Whip.
Mix sugar and cream cheese with mixer until smooth. Stir in other tub of Cool Whip, then mix with other cake mixture.
Slice strawberries and mix with glaze.
Layer in punch bowl, starting with cake mixture, then strawberry mixture.
Continue layers, ending with strawberry mixture on top.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
In a measuring cup, mix milk, vinegar and soda.
Add flour alternately with milk mixture to shortening mixture.
Add apples.
Grease 2 loaf pans and divide mixture into the 2 pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spread topping mixture on loaves when hot:

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Cook and drain ground beef; add mustard, catsup and onions to your liking; mix well.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Put a layer of cheese (any kind) on top.
Place canned biscuits on top of cheese, covering completely.
Cook slow until biscuits are brown.

title: squash and cheese casserole
directions: Mix together the eggs and squash.
Combine with flour, butter, bell pepper, onion, sugar, milk, salt, pepper, 3/4 cup cheese and bread.
Place mixture in greased casserole and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and the cracker crumbs; bake 20 minutes longer.

title: oatmeal maple cookies
directions: Beat shortening, maple syrup and egg.
Sift together salt, flour and baking powder.
Add to syrup mixture alternating with milk.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Frost with Maple Syrup Frosting.

title: melt away bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Cut in oleo like coarse corn meal.
Spread mixture in ungreased jelly roll pan and up sides 1-inch.
Cover with 2 cans peach pie filling.
Beat until stiff egg whites, cream of tartar and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread over peaches and sprinkle 1/2 cup walnuts over top.
Bake until golden brown at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Cook ground beef; drain off fat.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and undrained mushrooms.
Mix well and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni; drain and rinse with cold water.
Pour half of the shells into deep casserole.
Cover with half the tomato meat sauce.
Spread half the sour cream over sauce.
Top with slices of Provolone cheese.
Repeat, ending with slices of Mozzarella cheese.
Cover casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove cover and continue baking until cheese melts and browns lightly.
Serves at least 8.

title: quick chicken
directions: Combine onion, garlic, soy sauce and oil.
Cook 1 minute. Stir in rice, orange juice, water and water chestnuts.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and mushrooms.
Add chicken.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Set aside.
Saute chuck in 1 tablespoon butter until brown.
Stir in tomato sauce and remove from heat.
In a separate bowl, combine cheeses, sour cream, scallions and green pepper.

title: mexican casserole dip
directions: Layer refried beans, ground beef, sauce and cheese.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Serve on Tostitos chips with tomatoes and lettuce.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in pineapple, sour cream and lemon juice.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and comes to boiling.
Cook 2 minutes.
Stir small amount of mixture into egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Cool to room temperature and spoon into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with vanilla and cream of tartar to soft peaks.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff and glossy.
Spread top of pie; seal to edge of pastry.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dot's hot pepper relish
directions: Boil all ingredients except Certo and remove from heat for 20 minutes. Heat again to rolling boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; let stand 2 minutes. Add Certo and stir until mixture thickens. Pour into small jars and seal.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and egg.
Form a crust in buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Cook ground beef and drain. Stir in sauce, sugar and oregano.
Heat through. Put meat in crust on top of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake for 5 more minutes.

title: white eagles' mushroom barley soup
directions: Cook barley in water, covered, for 50 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add vegetables and simmer about 15 minutes, covered, or until tender.
Add beef broth and cream of mushroom soup. Simmer and stir well a few minutes.
If too thick, add a little more water.
If too thin, add a little instant Potato Buds.

title: sour cream vegetable dip
directions: Drain sour cream through a double layer of cheesecloth in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Discard liquid.
Add the other ingredients to sour cream.
Cover dip and refrigerate for a few hours for flavors to blend.
Serve with cut up raw vegetables. Makes 1 cup.

title: canned okra
directions: Cover with water.
Let it come to a boil (not over 1 minute). Put in jars and seal.
Be sure to use canning salt and vinegar. When you open a jar to cook, drain and rinse well with cold water. Let drain well, then batter and fry or put in stews.

title: chicken broccoli rice
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice in a saucepan.
Cook until blended.
Place rice in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chicken and broccoli on top.
Pour on soup mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Add bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage and potato hubble-bubble
directions: Place potato slices in an ovenproof dish.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry.
Add chopped onion and sausages, cut in half, and fry for 5 minutes.
Remove from frying pan and place on top of potatoes.
Beat eggs, milk and grated cheese together; add salt and pepper.
Pour into dish with the rest of the ingredients. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, fry sausage until cooked.
Drain sausage on paper towel.
Save 2 tablespoons sausage grease.
Saute onion and pepper in this for 2 to 3 minutes.
Slice sausage links.
Combine cheese and flour.
Stir in sausage slices, green pepper and onions.
Spread in pie crust shell.

title: banana split cake
directions: Cut cake in 3 layers.
Whip the whipping cream and chocolate pudding.
Layer cake, frosting, bananas and nuts.
Repeat second layer.
Last, layer pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Frost sides. Top with whole cherries.

title: swedish sweet pickles
directions: Drain dill pickles.
Place in large pan or bowl.
Add sugar and vinegar; stir to mix.
Add bag of spices; mix again for 3 days. Mix often.	Do not refrigerate.
After 3 days, pickles will be crisp and sweet.
Place in covered jars and refrigerate. Delicious.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter with a wooden spoon.
Add the sugar and honey and beat until creamy and light.
Add the eggs one at a time, then thoroughly mix in the bananas.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt and blend thoroughly into the mixture.
Finally fold in the nuts.
Butter a 12 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan and pour in the batter.
Bake in 350° oven, 1 hour or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in sugar until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill until consistency of egg whites.
Fold in pineapple, cranberries, orange rind, oranges, apples and pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: hot creole seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Cover and shake mixture until well blended.
Store in airtight container.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease bottoms of loaf pans.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool slightly, then remove from pans and cool completely.
Wrap and refrigerate.

title: apple mint tea
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a pitcher; pour in water. Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Remove and discard tea bag and mint leaves.
Add apple juice.
Serve over ice and garnish each glass with a lemon slice and mint sprig.
Contains 63 calories per cup.

title: onion casserole
directions: Layer steamed onions, soup and cheese in buttered dish or pan. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sukiyaki skillet
directions: Cut stew meat into thin slices.
Brown meat and onions in oil in a large skillet.
Cover and cook slowly about 10 minutes.
Add rice, water, salt and mushrooms with their liquid.
Cover and cook slowly until rice is tender, about 25 minutes.
Add pepper, celery, bean sprouts, spinach, soy sauce and sugar.
Cover and cook until spinach is tender, 5 to 8 minutes.
Do not overcook; vegetables should be crisp.
Toss lightly to mix ingredients. Serve with extra soy sauce if desired.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook mixture until it forms spinning hairs.
Add a pinch of soda and 2 to 3 drops vinegar.
Mix with 8 to 12 quarts popped corn.
Butter hands and form balls.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend well mayonnaise and cream of chicken soup.
Then add the chicken, celery and almonds.
Put in casserole; sprinkle potato chips, almonds and Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake in a 300° oven for 40 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a casserole dish add rice, broth, soup, butter, worcestershire sauce. Bake covered 1 hr. Stir about after 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Line quiche pan with pie crust.
Bake 5 minutes at 400°. Combine all ingredients.
Spoon mixture into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: indian spinach salad
directions: In jar combine vinegar, oil, chutney, sugar, salt, curry powder and mustard.
Cover and chill.
Tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Place in salad bowl, top with apples and raisins.
Shake chilled dressing well.
Pour over salad and toss.

title: pecan toffee
directions: Line 9-inch square baking dish or pan with foil, overlapping sides.
Butter foil.
Melt butter in heavy medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add sugar and cream of tartar and stir until sugar dissolves.
Increase heat to medium-high.
Brush down sides of pan with wet pastry brush.
Cook to 310°, stirring occasionally, about 11 minutes.
Immediately pour toffee into pan, tipping to cover foil evenly.
Let stand 1 minute.
Spread chocolate with back of spoon over toffee until melted and smooth.
Sprinkle with pecans. Refrigerate until firm.
Remove from pan and break into pieces. Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: cut out cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and salt.
Add baking soda and flour.
Do not make too stiff; put in refrigerator and chill for 6 hours.
Roll out and cut dough in shapes.
Bake for 8-10 minutes at 325-350°.
Decorate.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Mix 2 cups flour with white raisins. Mix all ingredients except egg whites in large mixing bowl. Fold stiffly beaten egg whites into mixture.
Bake for 3 hours at 250°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Put in pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg over the top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: frosted coffee fudge
directions: Combine sugar, coffee powder, salt, milk, cream and corn syrup in 3-quart heavy saucepan, buttered. Bring mixture to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
(If sugar crystals form on sides of pan, wipe off.)
Continue cooking, without stirring, over low heat to a soft boil stage (236°). Remove from heat. Add margarine and vanilla.
Do not stir. Cool, without stirring, until lukewarm (110°).
Beat until candy thickens. Pour into buttered pan.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler over water. Spread over cooled fudge.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Cool, then cut.

title: may wine
directions: Pick any damaged or withered leaves from the woodruff and put the whole bunch, including stems and flowers into a punch bowl or tall glass jug.
Pour over the wine.
Gently heat the sugar and water in a small pan and stir until the sugar has dissolved.
Cool a little, then stir into the bowl of wine.
Cover closely with a plate or sheet of foil and chill in refrigerator for an hour or longer.
Before serving, peel the orange and slice the flesh thinly.
Add the orange slices to the punch.

title: scampi-style shrimp
directions: In large skillet, over medium-high heat, cook and stir onion and garlic in margarine and oil 1 minute.
Add shrimp; cook and stir until shrimp are pink.
Add lemon and salt; heat through. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: banana slush
directions: Combine all ingredients except bananas and ice in a blender and blend on high speed for 15 seconds or until sugar is dissolved.
Add bananas and ice.
Blend until ice is crushed. Pour into two 16 ounce glasses.
Add a straw and serve.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except biscuits, butter and cornmeal.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Dip biscuits in melted butter, then cornmeal. Bake an additional 20 minutes, or until biscuits are brown. Freezes well.
Add biscuits later.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steaks in cubes; roll in flour.
Heat butter; brown steak and onion.
Add remaining ingredients, except sour cream; cook slowly.
Add sour cream just before serving.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: maple flavored syrup
directions: Combine sugars, corn syrup and water.
Stir until dissolved, then bring to a boil in a heavy saucepan.
Cover and boil gently, 10 minutes.
Do not stir!
Remove from heat and allow to cool. When cool, add the vanilla and maple flavoring and stir only until mixed.
Store in the refrigerator.
Makes about 32 to 36 ounces.

title: hello dollies
directions: Pour condensed milk over layers last.
Bake at 350 degrees 25-30 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Drain meat after cooking.
Add all ingredients and simmer for an hour with lid on.
Delicious!

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer until blended except the flour.
Add flour and beat.
If beater is unable to beat, mix with hands.
Chill.
Roll out as usual with flour board and rolling pin.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches, or round layer pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Beat baking mix, sugar, cocoa, egg, milk, shortening and vanilla in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 4 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Carefully split cake to make 2 layers.
Spread bottom layer with preserves.
Spread 1 cup Chocolate Cream over preserves.
Top with second layer.
Frost top and sides of cake with remaining Chocolate Cream.
Garnish with cherries and sliced almonds, if desired.
Refrigerate any remaining torte.

title: frontier breakfast
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Layer with pie crust.
Brown sausage and green onion and drain.
Layer sausage and onion on top of pie crust.
Then layer picante sauce on top of meat and onion.
Beat eggs, add milk and beat again.
Then add everything else to milk and egg mixture.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sugar, then add flour, cinnamon, soda, salt, vanilla, apples and pecans.
Pour into greased tube pan and cook for 90 minutes at 325°.

title: christmas rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in two 8-inch layer pans. Cool.
Place cake layers, top side up, in 2 clean 8-inch layer pans. Prick each cake with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.

Meanwhile, dissolve each flavor gelatin separately in 1 cup boiling water. Carefully pour raspberry flavor gelatin over one cake layer and lime flavor gelatin over second cake layer. Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Dip one cake pan in warm water for 10 seconds, then unmold cake layer onto serving plate. Top with about 1 cup of the thawed whipped topping.
Unmold second cake layer and carefully place on first layer. Frost top and sides with remaining topping. Chill. Garnish with gumdrop holly leaves and berries.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and salt; set aside.
Over low heat, melt butter in a large skillet.
Add egg mixture and chopped dates.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and turn slightly brown, about 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal and nuts.
Cool in refrigerator until cold.
Shape into walnut size balls and roll in coconut or nuts or confectioners sugar.
Refrigerate to set cookies.

title: super brownies from jackie fay
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: gnocchi(potato pasta; kids will love to help!)
directions: Boil potatoes whole and unpeeled for about 40 minutes; drain and cool.
Peel and mash in a bowl.
Add garlic, flour, salt and seasoning.
Stir into soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface. Divide into 4 to 6 parts; shape into ropes about as thick as your finger.
Cut into 3/4-inch pieces and roll them on the tines of a fork.
Drop into boiling water.
Gnocchi will sink.
After 1 to 2 minutes, they rise to the top and are done.
Carefully drain; top with your favorite spaghetti sauce.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and evaporated milk.
Boil 9 minutes at full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool.
Cut in squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: peach dream
directions: In a large bowl, combine cottage cheese and dry peach jello. Stir and mix well.
Drain oranges and add with remaining ingredients.
Stir lightly to mix.
Serve on lettuce as salad or serve as dessert.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in greased loaf pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once, just until moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan.
Cool on rack or serve warm.

title: pineapple side dish
directions: Pour pineapple	with
juice
in long Pyrex dish and mix together flour
and
sugar.
Sprinkle over the pineapple.
Put cheese over
that,	then
crackers on top.	Melt margarine and pour over all.
Bake
at
for 30 minutes or until brown. Serve warm.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Grease & flour 10 x 13 pan.
Pour batter in pan & sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: skier's french toast
directions: Combine the corn syrup, butter and brown sugar in a small saucepan; simmer until syrupy.
Pour this mixture over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Slice bread into 10 (1 to 1 1/2-inch) thick slices.
Place over the sugar-butter mixture.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain well.
Saute onion in oleo.
Add onion, cheese and soup to broccoli.
Brown crushed crackers lightly in oleo which is left from sauteed onion, then sprinkle crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: coconut pie
directions: You may substitute 1/4 cup buttermilk for vinegar.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer in saucepan for 20 minutes.

title: chicken continental
directions: Sprinkle rice in casserole.
Put 1/2 can of soup over rice. Brown chicken and place over rice.
Cover with remaining soup and other ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cold oriental salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soy sauce, lemon juice, curry powder and garlic salt; mix well, then add tuna, celery, peas, onions and water chestnuts.
Mix well and let set in refrigerator for 8 hours.
At serving time, add chow mein noodles and almonds.
Serve cold.
Makes large salad.

title: german apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in bowl.
Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Beat on low speed until well blended.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Spoon in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until tested done.

title: watercress salad with creamy garlic dressing
directions: Combine mayonnaise, 2 tablespoons water, lemon juice, 1/4 salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and garlic.
Cut stems of watercress. Peel cucumber; remove the seeds and cut into slices.
Peel carrot and grate.
Pour dressing on top.

title: scalloped turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In medium saucepan, combine butter with water and heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Add stuffing and parsley.
Toss lightly until stuffing is moistened.
Set aside.

title: vegetable cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: advent wreath cake
directions: Combine and beat for 4 minutes.
Place in well-greased 12-cup ring mold or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Frost with green frosting and green coconut if desired.
Red hots can be used for holly berries.
Put 4 candles for the first Sunday of Advent.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Clean giblets and neck of turkey.
Cook gently in salted water.
Neck and gizzards take at least 1 1/2 hours to cook; livers, 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove meat from neck and add to broth.
Finely chop liver and gizzard; add to broth.
Add seasonings.
To thicken gravy, allow about 1 tablespoon of flour per cup of broth and combine with a small amount of cold water; then add to broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Add eggs.

title: pineapple tarts
directions: In small bowl combine first 3 ingredients; mix at low speed until well blended.
Add flour and mix well.
Form dough into twelve balls.
Press dough into muffin tins.
Sprinkle nuts into each using half the nuts.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Add tomato paste, water, sugar, salt, bell pepper, black pepper and Tony Chachere's Creole seasoning to hamburger mixture. Mix together and simmer 1 hour.
Boil spaghetti; drain water off. Mix in meat sauce or serve meat sauce over spaghetti on individual plates.

title: baked walnut fudge
directions: Combine ingredients and beat until blended.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Set pan in a larger pan.
Pour hot water into pan so it surrounds small pan to the depth of 1-inch in a 350° oven.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
It's so good!

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Mix all ingredients together, excluding cabbage leaves and tomato sauce.
Rinse cabbage leaves and drop into boiling water for one minute or until limp.
Drain and pat leaves dry.
Put about 1/2 cup of meat mixture onto each leaf.
Fold it envelope style with seam side down onto a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan. Pour tomato sauce over cabbage rolls.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; cool.
Peel and shred coarsely.
In saucepan, over low heat, combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter, stirring occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes. turn into 2-quart greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
If made ahead and frozen, increase the baking time.
Serves 8.

title: black bean tortillas
directions: Saute onion and pepper until tender in chicken broth. Wash and drain black beans. Mash one can of black beans. Add beans and salsa.

Cook until thick. Place about 3 or 4 tablespoon of mixture on tortillas and roll up and folding ends in. Place in pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350 degrees. Sprinkle cheddar cheese on top and bake for 5 minutes. Serve on chopped lettuce and tomatoes topped with sour cream.

title: black-eyed chili
directions: Prepare black-eyed peas according to package directions.
Brown onions, ground beef and sausage; drain.
Add onion, beef and sausage to peas.
Add entire can, including liquid, of tomatoes. Add salt and cayenne pepper to taste.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Serve hot.

title: texhoma beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Pour over beans. Simmer until well blended.

title: 9 layer mexican dip
directions: Layer in oblong
baking
dish in the order given. Cover bottom of dish
with
chips.
Heat
refried
beans
and
cover chips. Brown hamburger
meat or boiled chicken and cover beans (onions and green
pepper
may
be	cooked	with meat).
Layer jalapenos, then
mushrooms, sour cream and lettuce (washed and dried).
Pour salsa over and top with Cheddar cheese. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until cheese is melted. Dip can be as hot or mild
as
you like by omitting jalapenos and using mild or hot salsa. Eat with remaining chips.

title: delicious apple cake
directions: Pour
sugar
over
apples;
let stand 20 minutes.
Sift flour, soda and salt together 3 times.
Add nutmeats to flour mixture. Pour
eggs
over
sugar
and
apples, then mix flour mixture.
Add oil, allspice and cinnamon.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325° in a tube pan.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, milk, baking chocolate and salt. Stir until mixture begins to boil.
Boil slowly to soft ball stage (236°).
Set pan in cold water and leave until cold.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat mixture until it becomes thick and creamy. Pour into buttered tin and, when set, cut in squares.
This recipe is 50 years old.

title: ham and split pea soup
directions: For Soup:
In large saucepot, combine peas, carrot, celery, onion, ham bone, water and pepper.
Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours until peas are soft.
Remove bone and cut away meat; discard bone and cut away meat; discard bone.
Cut ham into 1/4-inch cubes.
If desired, for a smoother soup, place vegetable mixture, in batches, in food processor or blender container; process until smooth.
Add ham and reheat soup, if necessary.

title: perfect peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients; add egg, tossing with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Drizzle with butter and shake cinnamon over the top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix (do not use mixer) until blended.
Drop small amounts on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Do not over-bake.)

title: easy soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add potato, water, tomato sauce, dry soup mix, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until done (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco tater skins
directions: Bake potatoes at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.
Reduce heat to 350°.
When potatoes are cool enough to handle, cut lengthwise into quarters.
Scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4 inch shell.
(Save pulp for another use.)
Combine the butter and taco seasoning; brush over both sides of potato skins.
Place skin side down on a greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with cheese, crumbled bacon and green onions.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is melted, and lightly browned.
Serve with salsa and sour cream, if desired.

title: fruitful muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups. Combine oats, flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill cup 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Arrange 1 package in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with peas. Mix soup, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, cheese, onion and eggs.
Pour half of mixture over broccoli and peas.
Add remaining broccoli; top with sauce.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Asparagus may be substituted for broccoli.)

title: faye's company chicken
directions: Wrap each breast with a slice of bacon and lay in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Bake at 200° for 4 hours.
Sprinkle with mushrooms and parsley.
Serve with rice.
(Sauce is sufficient to use as many as four more half breasts.)

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant whole.
Slit lengthwise 1-inch deep and 1 1/2-inches apart.
Salt entire eggplant.
Stuff into slits the thinly sliced sweet onions, slices of fresh garlic, small slices of brick Parmesan cheese and last with slices of raw bacon.
Salt again.
Place small amount of olive oil and 1/4 cup water in bottom of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
(Longer for more than 1 eggplant.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix with milk in saucepan.
Add peanut butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat until full boil.
Cool cooked pudding 5 to 7 minutes; stir twice.
Pour into pie shell. Chill 3 hours.

title: mexicorn casserole
directions: Brown meat and chopped onion; drain.
Add rest of ingredients and cook on top of stove for 35 minutes.
Serve over noodles cooked in salt water.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to jello with 1/2 cup pineapple juice. Refrigerate and allow to firm slightly.
Stir in pineapple and pie filling.
Allow to jell completely.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla together.
Spread over top.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: party chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce or as spread for open-faced sandwiches.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake one hour at 350° or combine in crock-pot and cook for several hours.
I often use one pound of hamburger or bacon.
You can also vary the size of the cans of beans and kinds of beans.

title: creamed chipped beef
directions: Soak beef in cold water 15 minutes (drain).
Pick into thin pieces.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in pan.
Put in beef and brown. Add milk and cream.
Bring to
boil; thicken with flour, mixed to a smooth paste with balance of butter (1 tablespoon).
Stir constantly until it boils.
Serve over toast.
Serves 6.

title: candied yams
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in a large iron skillet and stir until blended.
Add raisins and yams (cut) and simmer for a few minutes until hot, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and 1/2 cup water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans.
Stir until mixture becomes creamy.
Turn onto waxed paper and separate pecans with fork.
Let dry.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix until everything is moist, then add nuts.
Stir in cranberries with a spoon last.
Bake in
moderate oven for about 1 hour or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: best refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine boiling water, shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add eggs.
Sprinkle yeast into lukewarm water; stir until dissolved.
Combine with egg mixture.
Blend in flour.
Cover and refrigerate.
This will keep 1 week to 10 days.
About 3 hours before using rolls, shape, using only enough extra flour to make them easy to handle.
Place on greased pan and allow to rise 3 hours at room temperature or until double in bulk.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on French bread.
Broil to warm and melted.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour over bananas and wafers in large pan.
Best to let sit two or three hours.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients in large baking dish.
Add topping of 2 cups crushed cornflakes and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cheese crisp
directions: Slice apples; place in greased baking dish.
Pour water and lemon juice on top.
In a separate bowl, combine the sugar, cinnamon, flour, butter or margarine and cheese until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bayou brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sunburst yams
directions: Halve oranges; squeeze, reserving 1/4 cup of juice.
Remove pulp.
Beat yams until smooth.
Beat in juice, brown sugar and 3 tablespoons of butter.
Spoon mixture into orange shells.
Brush edges with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° until heated through, 20 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with coconut, mint sprig and cherry.

title: tea bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients then add tea and raisins.
Bake 350°, 1 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add eggs and vanilla to rice mixture. Add raisins. Pour into buttered baking dish and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Bake uncovered.

title: green chile cheese bites
directions: Butter bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread chiles on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cheese over chiles.
Pour eggs over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 30 minutes or until firm when pan is shaken.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve hot.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
When mixture is syrupy, add remaining ingredients.
Fold in and mix.

title: baked steak
directions: Put flour, salt and pepper into a bowl or flat dish.
Mix together.
Take steak and roll steak in mixture, getting the steak good and coated on both sides.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan (8 x 8-inch).
In medium mixing bowl, blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs. Beat well with spoon.

title: baked macaroni with apples
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine apples, sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Put aside.
Place 1/4 of the noodles into the greased pan.
Spread 1/4 of the apple mixture over them and sprinkle with melted butter.
This is the first layer.
Make 3 more layers, sprinkling each with melted butter.
Spread sour cream over the top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: oatmeal flatbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Divide dough into egg-sized balls and roll into very, very thin sheets on a flour-covered pastry cloth.
Transfer to cookie sheets and bake at 325° to 350° until light tan.
It does not need to be turned over. Store in closed container to keep dry.
Serve with butter.

title: corn and shrimp soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oleo.
Blend cream cheese and milk in a blender.
Add this and all other ingredients together.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Delicious.

title: chicken-fruit salad
directions: Remove 6 outer leaves of lettuce; wash and set aside.
Chop remaining lettuce; set aside.
Peel and seed avocado.
Slice half of avocado and set slices aside.
Chop remaining avocado.
Combine chopped lettuce, chopped avocado, chicken and last 5 ingredients. Toss gently.
Serve on reserved lettuce leaves and garnish with avocado slices.

title: hot cajun pickles
directions: Drain all juice from pickles and throw away.
Slice all pickles. Put 1/2 of sliced pickles back in jar. Add 3 cups sugar and 10 cloves.
Add 2nd half of pickles to jar. Add last 3 cups of sugar, 10 cloves and all the Tabasco sauce. Add garlic and onion. Shake jar twice a day for 7 days. Put in refrigerator.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter; add tomatoes.
Add the chicken, seasonings and can of soup.
Mix well.
Layer the meat mixture in a casserole dish with the crushed taco chips and cheese, ending with a layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: miracle cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Flatten with fork. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cherries in the snow cake
directions: Mix cream cheese with sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread thin layer of mixture on cake plate.
Slice cake into 3 layers.
Ice each layer with mixture and then 1/3 of the pie filling. Refrigerate 8 hours before serving.

title: italian vegetable pizza squares
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Heat oil in medium nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add broccoli, cauliflower, carrot and garlic; cook 2 to 6 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in green onions.
Unroll dough; press in greased pan.
Bake for 6 to 9 minutes or until light golden brown.
Top with Mozzarella cheese, vegetable mixture, tomatoes, Italian seasoning and Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and crust is deep golden brown.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine vegetables, tossing lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly. Cover and chill overnight.
Drain well to serve.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: a quick snack
directions: Cut celery sticks in three equal parts.
Spread peanut butter into each celery stick.
Space raisins equal distance on top of peanut butter.

title: spinach stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook and stir rosemary, sage, oregano, thyme and garlic and oil in small sauce pan over medium heat about one minute. Do not let herbs turn brown. Add tomatoes; reduce heat to low. Simmer 10 minutes. Combine spinach, cheese and bread crumbs in a medium bowl. Fold in egg whites. Stuff manicotti with spinach mixture. Place 1/3 of the tomato mixture on bottom of 9 by 13 inch pan. Arrange manicotti in pan. Pour remaining tomato mixture over manicotti. Cover with foil. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Garnish with yellow pepper rings and sage sprig.

title: texas leagues
directions: In saucepan, bring to boil cocoa, margarine and milk.
Remove from heat; add confectioners sugar and beat with mixer.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour hot frosting over hot cake.

title: bacon and cheese omelet
directions: Cook bacon ahead and break into several pieces.
Pour well beaten eggs onto hot pan.
Immediately add cheese that has been quartered and bacon on top of cooking eggs.
Fold over and finish cooking. You may also use ham or sausage.

title: shrimp charleston
directions: Prepare salad dressing according to package directions, omitting the water and replacing it with vinegar.
Place ingredients in deep bowl.
Pour the prepared dressing over all and marinate overnight.
Stir occasionally but carefully so as not to break artichokes.
This may be served, drained on a head of lettuce for lunch, or as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: party chicken
directions: Line a baking dish with dried beef or ham.
Top with chicken. Put bacon slices on top of chicken.
Mix soup, sour cream and mushrooms; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 250°.

title: pastry
directions: Cut Crisco into flour until pieces are size of peas.
Add 1 egg and vinegar.
Mix a little and add water.
If it feels too sticky, add a little more flour.
Roll out on floured surface, adding a little more flour.
Roll around rolling pin to lift onto pie dish. Makes 2 layers.
Any left over, freeze until you have enough for 1 more layer.
Bake at 425° for about 12 minutes or according to pie directions.

title: russian tea(diabetic)
directions: Mix all this together and put in airtight jar.
Then just add to boiling water as you need to.
Can be made just by the cup.

title: baked coconut custard
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; add butter.
Cream well.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hidden valley cheese ball
directions: Cream dressing mix into softened cream cheese.
Stir in green onions and grated cheese.
Roll into ball.
Chill, then roll in pecans and parsley flakes.

title: canning vegetable soup
directions: In large kettle, mix first 4 ingredients, 3 cups water and 2 teaspoons salt.
Heat.
Add vegetables and boil 5 minutes.
Pour soup into hot jars, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Adjust lids and rings.
Process in pressure canner at 10 pounds pressure (for pints) 55 minutes; quarts 85 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: fudgy bonbons(yields 5 dozen tasty cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in condensed milk.
Stir in flour, nuts and vanilla until combined.
Cover each Kiss (Hug) completely with 1 level tablespoonful of dough.
Place cookies 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes. (Cookies will appear soft and shiny.)
Place wire rack on wax paper.
Put cookies on rack to cool.
Melt white chocolate and shortening, stir, in saucepan over low heat.
Drizzle over cookies.
Let cool.

title: magic cookies
directions: Cream together and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet or shape into 1-inch balls and press with a fork in crisscross design. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam before baking.

title: maple oatmeal bread
directions: In bread machine pan, place all ingredients in order suggested by manufacturer.
Select the basic bread setting.
Choose crust color and loaf size, if available.
Bake according to bread machine directions.
(Check dough after 5 minutes of mixing; add 1 to 2 Tbsp. water or flour, if needed.)
Yield:

title: leeks au gratin
directions: Cook leeks; place in baking dish.
In 1-quart saucepan over low heat, melt butter, stir in flour, mustard and salt until smooth. Gradually stir in milk; cook, stirring until thickened.
Stir in cheese until melted; pour mixture over leeks.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Broil to brown crumbs.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Melt the 2 tablespoons butter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup brown sugar over the butter, then sprinkle the nuts over that.
Arrange thin slices of unpeeled apples in rows over the sugar, butter and nuts.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and set aside.

title: snowball salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, sugar and lemon juice together. Add the bananas, pineapple, pecans and cherries.
To serve as a chilled salad, chill overnight.
To serve as a frozen salad, place in freezer until firm.
(Freeze in square cake pan; cut into small squares.)

title: double bean salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together with enough French dressing to moisten.

title: apricot souffle
directions: Combine Jell-O and hot water; mix in blender.
Add cream cheese and blend.
Add apricots, including liquid, and blend on "liquify."
Pour in mold and chill.
Garnish with extra apricots.

title: maude's coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture with milk, a little at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Bake in three 8-inch cake pans in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Frost cake.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Place in a baking dish and spread green beans on top.
Put Tater Tots on top of the green beans.
Beat soup and milk with mixer until smooth, then pour over casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: bride's punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid according to package directions with 2 cups sugar.
Mix Jell-O with 1 cup hot water and 4 cups cold water. Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale and sherbet, and chill.
Put sherbet in punch bowl.
Add juices.
Pour ginger ale in last.
Serves 35.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine everything in blender or food processor.
To prevent separating, add 4 Tbsp. mayonnaise.

title: casey's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
This can also be used as a plain pound cake by leaving the cocoa out and adding 3/4 cup more flour.

title: mike's favorite baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and season with salt and pepper.
Add next 7 ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Cook spaghetti, drain and add meat mixture.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese slices and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly and cheese is melted.

title: greek meatballs
directions: Moisten bread with water and squeeze out any excess water. Beat eggs by hand and add all ingredients to meat, mixing well. Rub a little corn oil on hands and form meat mixture into balls. Fry in a little corn oil.

title: vanilla-apricot bark
directions: Preparation:
Toast nuts 5 minutes in oven; snip apricots. In medium microwave-safe bowl, melt chips in microwave on High for 1 minute.
Remove and stir.
Return to microwave for 1 minute. Mix in apricots and nuts.
Spread mixture over foil-covered cookie sheet.
Garnish top of mixture with remaining 2 tablespoons apricots.
Push down in place.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Lift off foil; break into pieces.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and blanch pasta with salad oil.
Cool.
Cook together the sugar and vinegar.
Set aside to cool, then add ingredients and mix with cooled pasta.
Can be made one or two days ahead. (Use large shell mostaccioli noodles.)

title: asparagus rolls
directions: With rolling pin, flatten bread.
Combine Blue cheese, cream cheese and egg.
Mix well.
Spread on bread crumbs, covering to edges.
Place 1 asparagus spread on each slice.
Roll tightly. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine, egg, buttermilk and flavorings. Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and spray with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool to touch.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Set shells aside.
Combine potato pulp, yogurt and next 6 ingredients in a medium bowl; mash until light and fluffy.
Pipe or spoon mixture into shells.
Place potatoes on an ungreased baking sheet. Sprinkle with paprika and bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: three cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Spread on rye bread (cocktail).
Bake in oven for 10 minutes at 350° (until cheese melts).

title: taco salad
directions: Cut or tear lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Fry ground beef, drain fat and cool.
Drain kidney beans.
Keep all ingredients separate until just before serving time.
Combine ingredients in the order given.
Mix gently to blend all together.
Serve immediately.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Steam spinach.
Beat 4 eggs, 1/2 of milk, 1 cup Mozzarella and 1/2 cup Cheddar.
Add 1 package of spinach.
Pour into 1 pie shell.
Top with onions.
Repeat for 2nd pie shell.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Slice baked potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out about 3/4 of flesh and set aside for other recipes.
Set skins on cookie sheet and place in oven about 4 inches away from top element. Broil 8 minutes.
Remove skins from oven and sprinkle with cheese. Season well and add bacon and paprika.
Broil another 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve hot with sour cream, if desired.

title: plum cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and spices; stir well and add plums.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 60 minutes or tube pan for 60 minutes.
Cover it with foil before baking and remove foil 15 minutes before done.
Ice with any icing or sprinkle with powdered sugar after removing from pan.

title: snowflake ice cream
directions: Stir together ingredients and chill.
Then gather clean, freshly fallen snow.
A full 2-quart bowl should be enough. Lightly stirring, pour the cream mixture over the snow.
Then serve immediately.
Makes about 1/2 gallon.

title: nut balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, nut meats, and vanilla. Form into balls the size of a quarter.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 325° for 25-30 min., watching carefully to avoid over baking.
When done, roll in powdered sugar.
Store in an airtight can.
(Can make 5 times this recipe.)

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and drain.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add soy sauce and mix.
Add shrimp and vegetables and mix well.
Roll into egg roll wraps according to package directions. Deep fry until golden brown.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer all the ingredients and let set overnight (refrigerate). Mix together before serving.

title: brisket (sweet)
directions: Trim off every piece of fat from brisket.
Slice the onions thinly and brown in skillet to golden.
Place brisket in large roasting pan.
Cover brisket with browned onions, dash of salt, paprika and black pepper.
Sprinkle top with the chopped garlic cloves.
Add 1 cup water to pan.
Cover and cook at 250° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours (or until tender).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in casserole dish.
Add crushed Ritz crackers in melted butter.
Add cut up chicken.
Mix sour cream, chicken soup and broth; pour over chicken.
Crush the remainder of crackers and sprinkle over the top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: classic brooklyn egg cream
directions: Pour the milk into a 12-ounce chilled glass.
Spritz in the seltzer until a white head reaches the top of the glass.
Spoon in the syrup with a little wrist action.
Serves 1.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed; let cool.
Break cake into chunks. Put in punch bowl.
Pour pineapple over cake with juice.
Mix pudding following directions and pour over cake and pineapple. Add cherry pie filling.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Do not stir.

title: mama's chicken dressing
directions: Mix ingredients, adding enough sage and poultry seasonings to suit individual taste.
Add enough chicken broth to make real moist.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 450° until it sets up.

title: denver sandwich ring
directions: Mix well the pancake mix, oil, milk and egg. Add the ham, onion and green pepper. Drop by tablespoon in a circle on a cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: glenda's meat loaf
directions: Mix well. Place in loaf pan and top with ketchup. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer about 2 hours.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
This is great made in the crock-pot!

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Beat in milk gradually.
(You will need to add more milk to make it as thin as pancake batter.)
Add flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth.
Cook in skillet 3/4 full of hot oil.
Cook until that side is done.
Turn and cook the other side.
Remove and drain well.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream oil and sugar, then add eggs and beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, and add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add jam and condensed milk and pour into tube pan which has been greased and lined on bottom with waxed paper.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter; beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add whipped topping and confectioners sugar, beating until smooth.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Freeze or refrigerate 8 hours.
Garnish with chocolate shavings.

title: sour cream fruit pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes longer.
Topping is optional.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook roast and cut up fine.
Saute beef, sausage and onions for a few minutes.
Mix all meat together.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Stir frequently during cooking time.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, boil together brown sugar, 1 1/2 cups hot water, salt and baking soda for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, soak raisins in the 2 cups of very hot water. After syrup is cooked, put soaked raisins (with water) into hot syrup and thicken with a thin paste made of cornstarch, granulated sugar and some water. Cook until very thick and glossy. Remove from heat and stir in half and half. Stir until smooth and creamy. Pour into pie shells. Cool and refrigerate. Top with whipped cream.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: meat balls
directions: Soak crackers in milk.
Mix with meat, chopped onion and eggs. Form into balls.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, milk, eggs and corn together and set aside. Brown ground beef and drain.
Pour 1/2 of corn meal batter into greased 15 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put in layers next the cheese, meat, onion and pepper.
Pour on remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grapefruit, orange and lemon marmalade
directions: In the afternoon
shave
the
fruit skins very thin and about an inch
long.
Break inside in pieces, taking out seeds and inner core.
Measure
and
to
1	part
fruit, add 3 parts water.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning boil hard for ten minutes.
Then put
away until next morning.
Measure mixture, add 1 pound of sugar
to
each
pint.
There will be 6 or more pints according to size
of
fruit.
Place
on stove and boil hard for about 1 hour.
Do
not cover.
Test by cooling a few drops until it jells.

title: cheese roll
directions: Crumble
flour
and shortening.
Mix and add warm milk, yeast, eggs
and sugar.
Mix dough with wooden spoon or until dough doesn't
stick
to
bowl.
Chill in refrigerator 3 or 4 hours. Divide
dough into 4 parts.
Roll each into rectangle, fill
and fold
the
edges
over and seal (don't let edges of rolls touch when baking).
Let rise in warm place for 30 or 40 minutes.
Bake at
for 15 to 20 minutes, or until light brown.
Drizzle with powdered sugar icing, if desired.

title: tami's cucumber salad
directions: Make a little or a lot; depends on amount needed. Add onion, mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar to taste.

title: west virginia soup
directions: Mix together in large pot.
Add 1 tablespoon shortening (Crisco in can).
Cook until cabbage is tender.
Serve with crackers or corn bread.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in reserved chicken broth.
In butter, saute until soft the celery, onions and bell peppers.
Add tomatoes, mushroom soup and cheese.
Drain spaghetti; combine with vegetable mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and onions into a gallon jar.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over cucumber and onions.
Keep in refrigerator for three weeks.
Ready to eat after three weeks. Keep in refrigerator until used up.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put in microwave bowl and heat until chips are melted.
Add nuts and put in 6 x 8-inch dish.
When set, cut in squares.

title: bread pudding
directions: Slice rolls.
Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over rolls.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Grease a deep ovenproof dish.
Spread a layer of bread mixture in dish.
Sprinkle with raisins, almonds, apples, sugar and small pieces of butter.
Continue until all ingredients are used up.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: scotch meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour topping over meat loaf and cook 30 minutes.

title: cookie turtles
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, milk, chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Add combined dry ingredients and nuts to creamed mixture; mix well.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes or until set.
Cool and frost with:

title: lillie's baked beans
directions: Mix together first 12 ingredients and pour into 5-quart Dutch oven.
Place bacon on top.
Bake at 450° until bacon is done.
Will serve 25.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat tortillas until warm and pliable.
For filling: blend chicken, Monterey Jack and chopped onion in large bowl.
Fill Tortillas, roll and place seam side down in shallow glass casserole.
For topping: thoroughly mix soup, picante sauce and 2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese.
Spoon over enchiladas and cook uncovered in microwave on high 5 to 10 minutes or until heated through and cheese is bubbly.
Makes about 6 servings.
For conventional oven: Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup with mushrooms

title: vegetarian nachos
directions: Heat the refried beans.
On a large platter, assemble the ingredients in layers:
first the chips, then the beans, then the lettuce, tomatoes, onion, half the cheese, the salsa and the rest of the cheese.
Put in the broiler for 2 minutes and serve.

title: spaghetti or lasagna
directions: Lightly brown meat and drain well.
Mix oregano, meat, tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, onion, bell pepper, mushrooms, garlic and seasonings to make the sauce.
Cook sauce all day. Cook noodles and drain well.

title: corn salad
directions: Make dressing by mixing sour cream, mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, salts, sugar and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and toss to blend.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix together rice, broccoli, cheese, soups, mushrooms, sauteed celery and onions.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with French fried onion rings.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, coffee and milk; mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes (batter will be thick).
Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch cake pans or two 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool cakes 15 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool on wire rack.

title: spinach vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve with raw vegetables and crackers.

title: deer jerky
directions: Remove fat from deer meat and cut on grain into 1/4-inch strips.
Marinate in ingredients overnight.
Remove from marination.
Bake in warm oven for 4 hours, turning over after that time.
Bake it 4 more hours.
Need to bake the meat on racks covered with aluminum foil.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken until done, then cube.
Cook noodles in broth. Saute onion in oleo.
Add cheese and melt.
Add soup, partially drained Ro-Tel and chicken.
Drain noodles.
Add sour cream and noodles to mixture.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in melted fat in skillet over medium heat.
Add water, peppers and onions.
Simmer until tender.
Add pineapple with syrup, vinegar, soy sauce, salt and brown sugar mixed with cornstarch.
Bring to boiling point and simmer until sauce is thick and meat is tender.
Serve on rice.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs in water covering the eggs for 10 to 15 minutes. Peel off egg shell.
Slice eggs long way in 1/2.
Take yolks and add to a bowl.
Add Italian dressing mix to a paste.
Add mustard. Combine and take a spoonful and fill eggs.
Sprinkle paprika. Chill and serve.

title: ropats' tavern corned beef and cabbage
directions: Take ingredients and place in large pot.
Cover; slightly simmer 4 to 5 hours until tender.
Remove meat from liquid.
Keep warm.
Skim fat from liquid.
Add 6 medium potatoes, pared and 6 small carrots.
Cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add 6 cabbage wedges and cook 20 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain fluid from beans.
Mix all other ingredients.
Place beans and marinade mixture in large bowl with tight-fitting lid. Refrigerate at least 8 hours (stir now and then).

title: cheese, macaroni and hot dogs
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour and salt.
Blend in evaporated milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Add cheeses.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in macaroni and hot dog slices.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: steamed rice
directions: Put
all
ingredients, except rice, in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; add rice.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook 25 minutes. Serve with favorite dish.

title: baked-in chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla, apples and all other ingredients.
Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed (or greased and floured).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
May top with a large container of whipped topping if desired.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Place bread on bottom.
Layer all other ingredients:
sausage or ham, hash browns, Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: raggedy ann pudding
directions: Cut cake into small 1-inch pieces; cover bottom of 4-quart bowl with cake.
Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Cover cake in bowl with chocolate pudding.
Cover pudding with Cool Whip. Cover with vanilla pudding, then Cool Whip.
