Place a teaspoon of chocolate pudding to garnish the center of top layer of Cool Whip. Enjoy!

title: chicken divan #2
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until almost done.
Drain and arrange in buttered baking dish about 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inches. Place
cooked
chicken on top of broccoli.	Combine soup, milk, lemon
juice, curry powder and mayo.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Combine bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle over top.
Cook in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Empty milk into large bowl.
Stir in lemon juice.
Drain fruits.
Add only the fruits.
Add Cool Whip and coconut.
Stir well.
Pour into graham cracker pie crusts.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: parmesan noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain well. Pour butter over noodles; add garlic powder and parsley, tossing gently.
Place noodles in a serving dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: powdered sugar pound cake
directions: Cream the butter well.
Add sugar in small amounts at a time and cream after each addition.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each egg, 1 minute.
(Use electric mixer for creaming and beating.)
Add flour and continue beating.
Add vanilla and mix.
Bake in tube pan that has been greased well and has 3 layers of paper, cut to fit bottom.
All 3 layers of paper should be greased.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.
Take cake from pan and wrap in cloth while warm.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all together except soup or juice.
Make into patties. Roll in flour.
Brown in fat on both sides.
Place in casserole. Pour soup or juice over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spinach and mushroom casserole
directions: Wash and chop spinach.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add half and half and slowly heat to boiling.
Cook 5 minutes.
Arrange layers of spinach and layers of sauce in buttered baking dish, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: a la carte green salad(one recipe, one thousand salads)
directions: Choose one from each category. Tear lettuce or spinach into pieces. Slice onions into ringlets or chop. Slice fruit if desired. Toast nuts if desired. Mix, serve with dressing on the side.

title: rouladen
directions: Tenderize steak.
Cut in triangles; spread with mustard, slice of onion, strip of bacon and slice of dill pickle.
Roll and fasten with toothpick.
Braise in hot skillet.
Add water and save liquid.
Remove toothpicks and put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour soup and tomato sauce with reserved liquid over meat.
Bake in oven at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: chicken, shrimp or sausage sauce piquant
directions: Fry sausage until brown; add 1 cup water, little at a time and then other ingredients.
Add another cup water and cook until done to suit your taste.

title: creamed mushrooms(recipe for diabetics)
directions: Add soup mix to water; boil gently, stirring now and then, for about 10 minutes.
Saute mushrooms in margarine in large skillet until browned on all sides.
Pour soup and lemon juice over mushrooms.
Season with salt and pepper.
Yields 6 cups.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift flour.
Re-sift with sugar and salt.
In saucepan, mix and bring to boil oleo, cocoa and water and while hot, pour over flour and sugar mixture.
In other bowl, combine eggs, baking soda, milk, lemon and vanilla.
Combine both mixtures and mix well.
On a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch sheet pan, bake at 350° for 20 to 23 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry crunch
directions: Place berries in a 2-quart baking dish, spreading evenly. Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Beat cream cheese and sugar together until smooth. Add eggs, vanilla and salt; beat until well blended. Place crust on baking sheet and pour filling into crust. Drop melted chocolate by teaspoonfuls onto filling.
Swirl chocolate into filling with tip of knife. Bake on baking sheet for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes clean. Cool; chill about 3 hours. Serves 8.

title: green salad
directions: Put
cottage
cheese and pineapple in blender and blend until smooth.
Dissolve
Jell-O
in boiling water and combine with pineapple
mixture.
Pour into mold and chill until firm. Good and fast!

title: superfast cobbler
directions: Pitted cherries or sliced peaches can be substituted for blackberries.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to unsweetened fruit.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in an 8-inch baking pan in oven.
Place blackberries and juice in small saucepan placed over low heat until heated through.
Combine flour, sugar and milk in bowl; blend well.
Pour into baking pan with melted butter; do not stir. Spoon blackberries and juice evenly over batter; do not stir. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with cream.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with cut up chicken breasts; sprinkle onion on top.
Mix soup and water and pour over chicken. Mix stuffing according to package directions and put on top of chicken-soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: camper's potatoes
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8-inch glass pan, 1 minute on High in microwave.
Slice onion into rings.
Toss potatoes and onions in melted butter.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt; stir well so that salt does not sit on top.
Cover dish with plastic wrap. Microwave for 12 to 15 minutes. Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes. Serves 6.

title: tab-boo-leh(parsley and wheat salad)
directions: Combine ingredients in deep bowl.
Toss together and serve with Pita bread.
Add more lemon juice, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork. Add 1/2 cup water; cover and simmer until tender. Add more water if necessary.

Drain pineapple, reserve syrup. Combine sugar and cornstarch, add pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce and salt. Add to pork; cook and stir until gravy thickens. Add pineapple, green pepper and onion; cook about 10 minutes. Serve over rice. Makes 7 servings.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in a large bowl with enough broth to soften bread crumbs. Add the chicken (after taking it off the bones and cut into small pieces).
Add 2 cups sweet milk. Pour into casserole dish and bake at 450° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: lord charley's creamed spinach
directions: Combine water, onion flakes and spinach and bring to a boil. Cook until spinach is thawed.
Drain and set aside.

title: verda layman's dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with layer of pineapple, sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple and drizzle melted butter or margarine over cake mix. Sprinkle coconut and pecans over top and bake in preheated 325° oven for one hour.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Brown veal, onion and garlic in hot, heavy skillet.
Add all other seasonings, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: haystack cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter for 3 minutes.
Stir often. Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, coconut, graham cracker crumbs and nuts.
Mix well.
Spoon onto wax paper to cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Place dish in a shallow pan of water and bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Serve immediately.

title: cheese cake
directions: Using a fork, mix together cake mix, egg and melted butter. Pat out evenly in cake pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry-cherry salad
directions: Dissolve unflavored gelatin in cold water.
Pour boiling water over lemon gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add unflavored gelatin and blend.
Set aside 1/2 cup gelatin mixture to cool.
Heat remaining mixture with cranberry sauce until sauce is melted. Drain cherries, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups; add cranberry mixture.
Chill until partially set.

title: southern peach cobbler
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in a 10 x 10-inch pan.
Pour cobbler mixture over butter; add the fruit. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown. May use other fruits.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with bread.
Brown sausage and spread on top of bread and then top with cheese.
Beat eggs.
Add salt, dry mustard and milk and pour on top of cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dee's pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift together and fold into pumpkin mixture the next 6 ingredients.
Spread in greased or wax paper lined jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on a towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Start at narrow end and roll towel and cake together.
Cool, not cold, just cool.

title: bulgogie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beef, in a large bowl.
Add the beef to the mixture.
Cooking in a barbecue grill will be the best.
Serves 4 persons.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine sugar, oleo, pumpkin, vanilla and eggs.
Blend well.
Stir in raisins and chopped nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart and bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from cooking sheet immediately.
Cool.

title: glazed boston shoulder
directions: Place meat on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Roast at 325° for 4 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Remove meat; spoon on sauce.
Roast for 15 more minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken. Remove bones.
Line pan with Doritos, then layer with chicken.
Pour mixture on top of chicken.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Add onion and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and cheese.
Toss the two mixtures. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crock-pot chili con carne
directions: In a heavy skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is browned. Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer in crock-pot 4 to 6 hours.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Roll one
slice
of
dried beef inside each breast half and secure
with a toothpick.
Place in a shallow baking dish. Mix soup
and sour cream well and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika
and
almonds.
Bake
for 4 hours at 275°, uncovered. Serve with rice.
Suitable for freezing.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Blend curry powder into the mayonnaise.
Gradually blend in the canned milk.
Add shrimp, green pepper, pimento and onion. Heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: bacon quiche
directions: Beat egg slightly. Mix in remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees until done or about 25 to 35 minutes.

title: tarragon chicken kabobs
directions: For marinade, in a screw-top jar combine grape juice, oil, lime juice, tarragon and garlic.
Cover and shake well.
Place chicken cubes in a plastic bag set in a shallow dish.
Pour marinade over chicken; close bag.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 4 hours, turning once to distribute marinade.
Drain chicken cubes, reserving marinade.

title: crock-pot chops and rice
directions: Brown the pork chops.
Mix all other ingredients together, except rice, and put in crock-pot with chops.
Cook on low for 4 hours.
Don't peek.
Make rice according to package directions. Serve over rice.

title: coconut supreme cake
directions: Prepare batter omitting oil.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour prepared cake batter and bake until done. Remove from oven.
While cake is still hot, spread coconut flakes over top.
Pour coconut syrup evenly over top. Refrigerate until completely cool, at least 2 hours.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add cabbage and onion.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook at medium heat about 15 minutes.
Stir often.

title: french vegetable salad
directions: Mix together vinegar, sugar, oil, mustard, celery seed, paprika and salt.
Add the drained cans of vegetables.
Mix well; chill for 4 hours or overnight.
Serves 15.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Remove skin and bones, if desired.
Flake with a fork and set aside.
Combine cracker crumbs and reserved liquid; let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in salmon, cornmeal, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape mixture into 6 patties.
Pour 1/4-inch oil into a large, heavy skillet.
Fry patties in hot oil over medium heat until browned. Drain patties on paper towel.
Yields 6 servings.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Toss together carrots, onion and green pepper.

title: lemon chicken stir-fry
directions: Fry chicken strips in margarine and garlic.
Add broccoli and carrot strips and toss.
Stir-fry for several minutes.
Add broth and bring to boil.
Add rice and pea pods.
Simmer until cooked. When finished, add the lemon juice and serve.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles until tender; drain.
Mix the egg noodles, peas, soup and tuna with 1/2 can of milk (soup can).
Put in casserole dish; sprinkle bread crumbs or crushed potato chips on top.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, Equal and garlic salt.
Combine remaining ingredients together.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over and mix well.

title: sausage cheese squares
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in baking pan or 10-inch round pie pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until it puffs in middle.
Cut in squares.

title: creamy crab dip
directions: Drain crabmeat; reserve 3 tablespoons liquid. Using foil, separate flaked crabmeat. Combine meat, liquid, cream cheese, onion juice and curry. Spread mixture in ovensafe dish. Sprinkle paprika, parsley and pecans on meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve hot with crackers.

title: layered salad
directions: Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Toss well just before serving.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Cream
butter
and sugar; add egg yolk and extract.
Add flour, make
balls and flatten with thumb.
Add jam or nut meat into thumbprint.
Place
on ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not allow cookies to brown.

title: povatica bread
directions: Mix yeast in the warm water, set aside.
Mix melted butter with milk, sugar, eggs and salt.
Then mix yeast mixture, flour and the melted butter/egg/sugar/milk/salt mixture.
Knead dough gently and rise for 2 1/2 to 3 hours in a greased bowl in a warm place.
Do not punch down, divide it into 4 parts.
Roll each part out as you would for cinnamon rolls.
Spread filling, about 6 tablespoons per loaf.
Then roll up into a loaf, place in a pan sprayed with non-stick vegetable spray.
Raise in a warm place about 30 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: homemade cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage; add Miracle Whip, sugar, vinegar and milk.
Mix well.
Let set in cool place for 5 to 10 minutes, then serve.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

title: baked salmon
directions: Beat eggs and add milk.
Mix with salmon that has been chopped into small pieces.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon coconut icebox cake
directions: Line the sides of a 9 x 13-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers. Place them standing up, with rounded sides against the pan. If necessary, trim the bottoms so they are level with the top of the pan. Cover the bottom of the pan with the remaining ladyfingers, cutting them any way you please to make them fit. (This layer will not show.) You may have leftover ladyfingers. Reserve them for another use.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and carrots. Blend in flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in coconut. Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until no imprint remains when touched lightly. Remove from baking sheet immediately and cool.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put marshmallows in.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Add to pan.
Spoon pie filling over top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: baked egg casserole
directions: Beat together eggs, milk and sugar. Add cheeses and butter; mix well. Add flour and baking powder; mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 glass pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients in a well-oiled casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: caesar dressing
directions: Coddle egg for exactly 60 seconds in simmering water.
Place egg in blender; while blending slowly, dribble in half of the oil. Add lemon juice, garlic and cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Slowly blend in the rest of the oil.
This dressing is best over romaine lettuce, but works well with all salads.

title: delightful ham rolls
directions: Have butcher slice boiled ham paper-thin.
Combine cream cheese, nuts and garlic.
Add a small amount of mayonnaise.
Do not get mixture too thin.

title: mistletoe punch
directions: Combine all ingredients through the grenadine in a punch bowl. Just before serving, add some ice cubes and gently stir in ginger ale.
Put a lemon slice and cherry in each punch cup and serve. Makes 30 cups.

title: easy roast and gravy
directions: Brown the roast in the oil on medium-high heat in a Dutch oven.
Top with onion slices and pour undiluted soup over the roast.
Put in 300° oven for 3 to 4 hours or put the browned meat, onion and soup in a crock-pot on high 3 to 4 hours.

title: cheese spread
directions: Put in blender or use hand mixer.
Blend until creamy.
Hollow out loaf of bread, breaking bread into small chunks for dipping. Put cheese spread into hollowed bread round.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburg and drain. Add the rest of the ingredients.

title: marinated london broil
directions: Score steak on both sides in a diamond pattern.
Brush mustard on both sides.
Place in a large shallow dish.
Combine Burgundy, lemon juice, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce; pour over steak. Cover and marinate 8 hours in the refrigerator.

title: spicy apple sour cream cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and spice in ungreased 8-inch square pan with a fork.
Add butter and stir until crumbly.
Set aside 1/2 cup.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar gradually.
Beat until glossy.
Fold in flour, salt, vanilla and coconut.
Line baking sheets with greased heavy brown paper. Drop coconut mixture by teaspoon on sheets.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: lenten spice cake
directions: In large saucepan, combine raisins or dried fruit, sugar, shortening, spices and salt (cloves may be omitted).
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Sift flour with baking powder and soda.
Blend into liquid mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Spread into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 325° oven for about 1 hour.
Cool in pan on rack.
This can also be baked in large-size cookie sheet 1-inch deep.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
This needs no icing.

title: hershey's holiday pie
directions: Melt candy bar and marshmallows in milk over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Let Cool.
Whip cream.
Mix with first mixture and put into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In 3-quart pan, bring water to a boil.
Add broccoli and onion and boil 10 minutes.
Add seasonings and shredded cheese; stir until melted.
Add milk, cream and butter.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Slowly add water to flour, stirring constantly, until texture is smooth.
Slowly add water, stirring rapidly.
Cook until soup is consistency of heavy cream.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend milk and egg.
Stir in corn and drop from a tablespoon into deep hot fat. Fry until brown, approximately 4 to 8 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: fresh peach chiffon pie
directions: Add sugar to peaches.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in hot water.
Cool and add to peach mixture, lemon juice and salt.
Chill.
When partially set, fold in whipped cream.
Pour in baked pie shell or crumb crust, if preferred.
Refrigerate.

title: bonnie butter cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease well.
Dust with flour 3 layer pans, 8 or 9-inch pans or 1 oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).

title: chocolate pie(microwave)
directions: Prepare crust or shell and place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Mix pudding with milk.
Cook on High 7 to 8 minutes, stirring often. Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate on hour.
Top with a whipped dessert topping when cool.

title: strawberry rhubarb crunch dessert
directions: Cut butter into flour and powdered sugar.
Pat into 9-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: edith's brown bread
directions: Mix together.
The batter will be stiff.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: caramel bars
directions: Heat
all
ingredients
(except the 2 cans of biscuits) until melted.
Separate biscuits into quarters.
Put in bowl. Toss mixture with biscuits lightly.
Put in greased tube pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter casserole; add ingredients.
Set casserole in another container with the bottom covered with water.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cherry cheese cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla. Beat until smooth.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown crumbled sausage in a heavy skillet; drain.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard and stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pepper nut spread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Makes a great sandwich spread for parties.

title: brazilian rice
directions: Wash and pick rice very well (preferably using long grain rice).
Melt shortening in a medium size skillet.
Use oil, lard or margarine, but not butter.
Fry the rice with onion, gently stirring with a wooden spoon, until the mixture has a swishing sound.
This takes about 10 minutes over a low flame and is a very important factor in producing the dry final product which is one of the prime requistes of Brazilian Rice.

title: sunny salad dressing
directions: Dissolve sugar in small amount of water.
Mix sugar with rest of ingredients.
Chill.
Serve over your favorite salad greens.

title: sarah christensen's steamed carrot-suet pudding(depression era)
directions: Wash and peel raw vegetables; put through medium meat grinder. Cut up as needed.
To fit grinder, grind also the beef suet and raisins.
Place in medium bowl; mix with other ingredients until well mixed.
Pack into 1-quart greased and floured mold or a small cloth bag that will hold a quart.
Tie bag and place in kettle with tight fitting lid.
Add boiling water to cover bag or if using mold, just enough boiling water to half way up mold.
Boil over medium heat for 2 hours with covered pot.
Serve warm with lemon sauce as topping.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes, onions and celery and place in water (just to cover). Cook slowly until tender. Fry and drain bacon while vegetables are cooking. Add bacon at end. Pour some of cooked vegetables into blender and blend. Then pour water off and add milk. Heat and cook until thickened. Add bacon, cheese and chives.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine butter, flour and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Mix well. Pat onto sides and bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Sift together granulated sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add eggs and lemon juice.
Spread over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: stoney creek chili
directions: Begin to brown beef.
Place beans into crock-pot.
Mix in the onion, garlic, pepper, chili powder and hot sauce of your choice. Drain beef after it has been browned and mix with the beans. Simmer until beans are tender.

title: buttermilk chocolate cake
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil. Blend in mixing bowl the next 3 ingredients and then add hot mixture. Slightly beat the remaining ingredients into the above mixture. Use a large cake roll pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat 3 eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in milk.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Mix.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken; remove skin and bones.
Cut into small pieces. Put back into liquid.
Cube several potatoes and a small onion. Add to chicken.
Then add the following: corn, butter beans and tomatoes.
Salt to taste.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Add salt and barely cover with water. Cook until tender and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a greased baking dish.
Cover top with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugars, vanilla, egg and water together. Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Blend into shortening mixture very well and then stir in oats.
On greased cookie sheet, spread 3 tablespoonfuls of dough to make a 3 1/2-inch circle. Make circles 2 1/2-inches apart.
Press candies into each. Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 375°.
I usually double this recipe.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Mix and let rhubarb and sugar stand overnight.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and add strawberry jello. Stir.
Cool and freeze.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In small	amount	of oil, fry taco shells until heated (a few seconds
on
each
side). Dip shells in enchilada sauce and fill each
shell with ground beef, grated cheese and onion.
Roll shell and place
in	9
x 13-inch baking dish.
Repeat until all shells
are	filled and pour remaining
sauce
over enchiladas.	Top
with
remaining cheese and onion.	Bake at 425° until heated,
about
minutes.

title: granny's german cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Mix all together well.
Put in refrigerator for a couple of hours.
Before serving, drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: applesauce squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Sift flour with baking soda and spices.
Beat in flour mixture alternately with applesauce.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven or until tester comes out clean. Cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: hot chinese chicken salad
directions: Roll chicken in corn starch.
Heat oil in frying pan or wok over high heat.
Add chicken and quickly brown. Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Add tomatoes, water chestnuts,
mushrooms, onions, celery and soy sauce. Stir. Reduce heat to simmer and cook five minutes.
Lightly toss chicken-vegetable mix with lettuce.
Serve hot with rice.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini seafood casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° until brown, or when knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with salad.

title: hash brown cheese bake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green beans with mushrooms and garlic
directions: Wash beans; remove ends.
Arrange in steamer basket; place over boiling water.
Cover and steam 12 minutes.
Remove beans and place in a single layer on paper towel to cool.
Melt margarine in a nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray.
Add mushrooms and garlic; cook 3 minutes.
Add beans, onion powder, salt and pepper; toss gently.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Yields 8 servings.

title: marinated asparagus and hearts of palm salad
directions: Steam asparagus for 4 minutes; drain and submerge in ice water to cool.
Drain well and combine with hearts of palm.
Mix vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper, then gradually drizzle in oil, whisking until blended well.
Pour over asparagus and hearts of palm; marinate for at least 8 hours.
Add tomatoes.

title: sugar-free fruit pie
directions: Mix together pineapple with juice and pudding.
Put cream cheese and pecans together. Then mix all together.
Can put in baked pie shell or graham cracker ready made shell.
Can put fresh strawberries on top.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slice and cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
In small dish, combine everything but bread crumbs and butter.
Spread over carrots.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: Melt butter; add the Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, onion, lemon juice and seasoned salt.
Saute about 3 to 4 minutes and remove from heat.
Alternate on skewers the chicken, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Brush with butter mixture and broil 3 to 5 minutes per side, turning often.
Roll in Parmesan cheese when done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese and cottage cheese; beat in sugar, eggs, cornstarch, flour, lemon juice, rind, vanilla, butter and sour cream.
Pour onto graham cracker crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let stand on oven rack 2 hours, then refrigerate.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cut flour tortillas in thin slices; layer in pan.
Add 1/2 of enchilada sauce on top of tortillas, then grated cheese, chopped olives, onion, salt, garlic and pepper.
Cook hamburger until brown.
Mix potatoes in with hamburger.
Layer ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cut tortillas in quarters.
Dip in small amount of hot oil for a few seconds, until slightly crisp.
Drain on paper towels. Brown meat, add garlic and onion.
Drain.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in bowl.
Add egg yolks and milk slowly, beating until batter is smooth.
Then add melted butter and fold in beaten egg whites.
Cook in waffle iron.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat butter about 30 seconds; add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add eggs one at a time; beat one minute after each.
Add dry ingredients and milk to beaten mixture and add peanut butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salmon balls
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
Drop into hot grease until golden brown.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine
all ingredients. Cook in heavy saucepan for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Pack in jars and seal.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: First Day: Wash cucumbers and pack in stone jar or in 2 (1 gallon) jars. Dissolve the salt in boiling water; add to cucumbers to cover. Let stand 24 hours.

title: toffee squares
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Measure flour and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until browned.
Spread chips on top and spread evenly.
Sprinkle on nuts.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and margarine. Beat vigorously with fork or spoon until stiff.
Spread in buttered dish.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: traditional corn bread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Lightly grease 13 X 9 X 2 inch baking dish or pan. Melt butter in skillet, saute celery and onion until tender, about 3 minutes. In large mixing bowl, combine corn bread, cook celery, bread, onion, sage and black pepper.
Stir broth and eggs into cornbread mixture, blend well. Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet almond chicken
directions: Place chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Combine jelly and next 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until jelly dissolves, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Let cool slightly.
Stir in almonds.
Pour half of jelly mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 additional minutes or until done.
Baste with remains of jelly. Broil chicken 4 inches from heat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beer batter bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and beer and put in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Melt butter and pour 4 tablespoons (half) of it on top of dough.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes, then pour remaining butter over top.
Continue baking 40 more minutes. Remove from oven; remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.
Best when toasted.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray small Corning Ware dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour apple pie filling into dish and sprinkle cinnamon on top of the apples.

title: never-fail brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Combine sugar and eggs.
Add chocolate mix to sugar mix.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts and chips (optional).
Spread in 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Fudge Frosting (recipe follows).

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange cupcake liners in cupcake tins. In small bowl, blend cheese, egg and sugar until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Sift together remaining sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Stir in water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Fill cupcake liners 1/3 full with chocolate batter.
Spoon cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon pudding cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with 1/2 cup milk.
Add remaining milk and the pudding mix.
Beat slowly with eggbeater just until well mixed, about 1 minute.
Do not overbeat.
Pour at once into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle crumbs lightly over top.
Chill about an hour.

title: chocolate refrigerator dessert
directions: Blend the graham crackers, soda crackers and margarine.
Put together in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix together the 2 packages of instant pudding and 2 cups milk.
Add the ice cream.
Beat well and pour over crumb mixture.
Top with the Cool Whip and a few more crumbs.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Boil unpeeled sweet potatoes in water until almost tender (about 15 to 20 minutes). Peel and slice about 1/4-inch thick when cooled (if using canned yams, just drain off the juice and slice them). Using a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of sliced sweet potatoes and apples, beginning with sweet potatoes and ending with apples (about 3 double layers). Cover each double layer with some of the brown sugar, salt, bits of butter and cinnamon (I usually mix these 4 ingredients together). Heat apple juice to boiling point. Combine cornstarch and water and add to juice, cooking until sauce is clear and thickened. Add honey. Spoon sauce over apples. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes to an hour or until apples are tender. Delicious with ham or turkey. Serves 8.

title: banana fluff salad
directions: Stir together flour, pecans, brown sugar and butter.
Spread evenly in a shallow pan.
Bake 350° for 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle half of crumbs in bottom of serving dish.
Slice bananas into crumbs.
Prepare pudding mix as directed.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Pour filling over bananas.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Chill several hours.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans. Preheat oven to 350°. Beat butter until smooth. Add sugar and eggs. Mix until light and fluffy. Add ripe, mashed bananas. Mix dry ingredients together and add slowly to banana mixture. Blend well. Pour into loaf pans. Bake 55 to 60 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean. Top of bread usually splits. Moist and delicious! Makes 2 loaves. Can freeze.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Press crescent rolls into a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet and bake for 7 to 8 minutes. Cool.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave directions:
In a 1-quart glass measure with handle, combine chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Cook on High 3 minutes or until chips melt, stirring after each 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into aluminum foil-lined or 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn out on board; peel off foil and cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake by directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. When done, punch holes in cake.
Empty Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Then empty cream of coconut over cake.
Spread Cool Whip on cake and sprinkle with coconut on top.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Combine and blend together for 1 minute.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill for 3 hours or more.

title: fancy potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, chives, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into greased 9-inch square pan, dot with butter and bake for 45 minutes at 300° until golden brown.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Pour scalded milk over bread crumbs.
Add onion, parsley, salt, pepper and eggs to bread crumb mixture.

title: my best pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs one
at
a
time,
beating
well after each.
Add the lemon juice and flavorings.
Add the flour and milk (begin and end with flour)
until
all	is used.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan (put wax paper in the bottom of pan). Put in a cold
oven	and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done when tested.
Cool
in
the
pan for a few minutes before removing.

title: swiss cheese spread (dip)
directions: Mix together and serve with crackers.
Excellent!

title: manhatten meatballs
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, eggs, onions and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch meatballs.
Brown in margarine, drain.
Place in casserole. Combine preserves and barbecue sauce; pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Makes about 5 dozen meatballs.
